title: church glass
directions: Melt together 4 Hershey bars, 12 ounces semi-sweet chocolate and 1 stick butter.
Add cup of nuts and 1/2 bag colored miniature marshmallows.
Roll 1/2 of roll in coconut.
Refrigerate for a few hours, then cut.

title: rice pudding with ice cream
directions: Bring to a boil the milk, sugar, salt, rice and ice cream. Turn flame to medium and cook 45 minutes or until rice is soft. Stir often.
In a small bowl, mix the 1 egg, vanilla and 1 cup of the hot rice until mixed well.
Add this to the hot pudding and cook for 15 minutes more.
Put into a bowl or 9 x 13 inch glass dish.
Let cool, then sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Refrigerate it until it is set firm.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: buckeyes(peanut butter candy topped with chocolate)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large container and mix with hands.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet in refrigerator and let harden (about 30 minutes).
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
With a toothpick, dip peanut butter balls into chocolate and place on wax paper to dry.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese with dressing mix.
Use one tortilla shell.
Spread small amount of mixture over shell.
Place 1 slice ham over mixture.
Spread small amount of mixture over ham.
Place one whole green onion over ham.
Roll up lengthwise.
Slice and place on a serving dish.
May also prepare without tortilla shells.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Mix drink powder, water and juice. Freeze.
Serve semi-thawed to slushy stage. Stir in cold ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add milk and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Serve immediately.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk, butter and coconut.
Pour into buttered pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
It will make its own crust.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, but apples.
Stir in apples by hand. Pour into 2 square cake pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: low-fat crispy oven-baked hush puppies
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk, oil and egg whites in a small bowl, stir well.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Over-mixing will cause tunnels and peaks to form in the hush puppies.
Spoon batter evenly into miniature (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans coated with vegetable cooking spray, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes or until hush puppies are lightly browned.
Remove from pans immediately.
Only 1.5 grams of fat per serving.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: sarena's spiced acorn squash
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Cut each squash in half and with a teaspoon, scrape out the seed and fibers.
In a small bowl combine the brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt and melted butter and stir them together thoroughly.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in water until done.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Save the broth.
In a pot, mix 2 cups of broth, celery soup, carrots and peas.
Place on stove and bring to a boil.
In a casserole dish, place chicken on bottom. Add soup mixture and stir.
Sprinkle eggs over soup mixture.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press into dish (the crust), dish size approximately 12 x 7 1/2-inch.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix well and cook until thick, about 3 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.

title: buttercream icing
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix margarine, shortening and vanilla. At medium speed, mix in sugar.
Add milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, until desired consistency is reached.
For truly white frosting, use 1 cup shortening instead of margarine and clear vanilla.
Great for cake decorating or sugar cookies.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Beat eggs, butter, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into ready made crust. Sprinkle bacon and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ethel whitt's baked cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a greased 6 x 6-inch pan.
Cook for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Mix syrup, sugar and eggs together.
Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Place in 400° oven and bake for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, cream and salt to soft ball stage (236°), stirring to keep from burning.
Add butter, pecans and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put stick of butter in a pan. Let melt at 350° in oven.
When butter melts, pour in 4 cups peaches.
Pour other ingredients over peaches; bake until brown.

title: western salad
directions: Combine all ingredients just before serving.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, eggs, salt and sugar together.
Add milk and corn.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over top.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 1 hour until lightly browned and firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Roll out and cut into circles.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Combine the crumbs and milk; bring to boiling point.
Add the butter and stir into the egg and sugar, beaten light, in the pudding dish.
Add vanilla; surround the dish with hot water in a cake tin.
Bake at 350° until a knife when inserted will come out clean, about 45 minutes.
If desired, add a cup of grated apple to the mixture.

title: cinnamon salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add red hot mixture, applesauce and lemon juice to Jell-O mixture.
Let ingredients set until syrupy (approximately 30 minutes).
Pour into Jell-O mold or bowl. Fold in small pieces of cream cheese and chopped nuts. Refrigerate until set.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: no fry chicken(low fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat baking sheet with 3 sprays vegetable oil.
Place chicken in bowl with ice water.
Place yogurt in separate bowl, breadcrumbs in large, reseal plastic bag.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix together crumbs, applesauce, sage, salt and catsup. Add beef;
mix	well.
Form into baking dish or pan.
Bake at 375° for
1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 8.	Garnish with whole, broiled or sauteed mushrooms.

title: baked fish
directions: Clean, wash and dry fish.
Rub inside and out with salt.
Place fish in a greased baking pan.
Brush with melted fat and lay slices of bacon over the top.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
If fish seems dry while baking, baste occasionally with drippings or melted fat.
Serve immediately on a hot platter, plain or with a sauce.
Serves 6.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits.
Can use any summer fruits, pick your favorites!
Sprinkle with sugar.
Squeeze lemon juice over fruit. Chill and serve.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie with buttercrunch topping
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, 1/3 cup flour and tapioca.
Mix strawberries and rhubarb together and add half of the mixture to the pastry lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with half the sugar, flour, tapioca mixture.
Repeat with remaining rhubarb and sugar mixture.
Cover with Buttercrunch Topping.
Flute edges. Cover with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Bake 50 minutes.
Best served with warm French vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown beef and next 3 ingredients; drain.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mash beans into mixture.
Heat, stirring often.
Add Tabasco.
Garnish with cheese.
Makes 3 1/2 cups for dipping with chips or crackers.
Won't last long.

title: depression chocolate cake
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add all liquids. Mix with a large spoon.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch or two layer cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Frost with chocolate/peanut butter frosting and enjoy!

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add beef and onions.
Cook until beef is cooked and onions tender.
Add soup, water, salt, pepper and rice.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 3 minutes.
In a 3-quart casserole, place cabbage at bottom.
Spoon beef mixture over cabbage.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Preboil rice.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans well.
Mix green beans, soup, milk and pepper.
Fold in half of the can of onions.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Put other half of can of onions on top of the casserole and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Velveeta, soup and chilies in a double boiler.
Combine ground beef and seasonings.
Cover with water.
Place over medium heat and stir often.
Cook until tender.

title: holiday chicken
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil.
Place in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be placed under broiler for a few minutes to brown if desired.

title: dutch babies (breakfast)
directions: Melt butter in cast iron skillet (or 10 inch baking dish).
In blender, put eggs, milk, flour and salt.
Blend.
Pour in skillet. Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Top with desired filling. Add whipped cream, syrup, etc.
Easy!
Like a big popover.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Will keep in refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Cook as needed.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12 cup muffin pan.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Crush 1/2 c. blueberries and add to batter.
Fold remaining berries into batter and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack and cool completely.

title: chocolate sprinkle coffee cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Completely mix in brown sugar and 3/4 cup butter with a fork until forms fine crumbs.
Remove 1 cup mixture for topping.
With remaining mixture, add milk, vanilla and egg.
Beat until smooth; pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish lightly floured.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix together 1 cup buttermilk with 1 teaspoon soda.
Add flour and mix alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in vanilla, pecans, coconut and beaten egg
whites.
Bake in 3 round 8-inch pans at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: green and white spinach lasagna(excellent)
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook lasagna noodles in a large amount of boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion in oil.
Drain off grease; add taco seasoning.
Mix and follow directions on package.

title: pudding cake(needs no icing)
directions: Prepare pudding mix with the milk as directed on label.
Stir in cake mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with morsels and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.
No frosting necessary!!

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls.
Mix
margarine,
mustard,
poppy seed and onion and spread on both sides.
Sprinkle with ham and replace tops. Heat and serve.

title: jello apples
directions: Peel apples, quarter and place in Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle Jell-O over apples.
Cook in microwave for 4 minutes or until tender.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine the flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.
With a rotary mixer, beat together the butter and sugar until they are smoothly blended.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
With a spoon, stir in the vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Alternately, stir the dry ingredients and the milk into zucchini mixture, including the nuts with the last addition.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread chips with knife as they melt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken parts in a greased casserole.
Mix together nuts, onion, creamed chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Spoon over top of chicken.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: homemade lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna with salt for 10 minutes.
Cook hamburger meat and drain, then put about 1 1/2 cups of Prego with hamburger until it boils.
After boiling, drain lasagna, then let it set in cold water.
Lay lasagna in pan.
First, a layer of lasagna; second, hamburger meat with Prego.
Third, a layer of both cheeses and the mushrooms, then repeat until finished.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion.
In casserole baking dish, combine cream of chicken, butter, flour, eggs and cream cheese; mix well. Add cooked broccoli and onions.
Mix in Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and add crushed potato chips, return and cook for 10 minutes.

title: marian's special chicken
directions: Spray large glass baking dish.
Place corned beef slices on pan.
Place chicken breasts on corned beef.
Roll chicken breasts. Wrap bacon around chicken breasts.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix with spoon and pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place
yeast
in
warm	water.	Cream
sugar and oil in large bowl (should have tight lid).
Add egg and cream little more.
Add yeast and water mixture.
Stir and add flour.
Mix well
with electric mixer.
Put airtight lid on bowl and keep in refrigerator.

title: pancakes from scratch
directions: Blend flour and sugar, combine milk, egg, stir until smooth.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. In a separate bowl blend together mayonnaise, salt, pepper, mustard, sugar and milk.
Stir into the first mixture and refrigerate. Before serving add cheese and tomatoes.

title: no crust chicken pie
directions: Pull chicken apart and place in baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and broth in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, mixing well.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Combine flour, buttermilk and margarine. Mix well.
Pour over top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: almond joy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and press into a pan.
Put almonds in center (optional).
Freeze 1 hour.
Melt 1/2 block paraffin and package of milk chocolate chips.
Dip and refreeze.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients, except for the cans of mushrooms and tomato soup, and shape into balls.
Then arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Drain sliced mushrooms and add enough water to this drained liquid to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add this 3/4 cup liquid to can of tomato soup and the sliced mushrooms and pour mixture over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done all the way through the meatballs.
Turn once during baking time.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix altogether in a large bowl.
Put into an airtight container.
Store in refrigerator.
Make muffins whenever needed. Can keep for 6 weeks.
Be sure to keep the lid on securely.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rye griddle cakes
directions: Sift the rye and wheat flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the milk, then eggs (well beaten).
Beat thoroughly and use all batter.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs, and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and chopped pecans.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except blueberries and Nut Topping. Using an electric mixer, beat 30 seconds on low speed.
Scrape bowl.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed; scrape bowl frequently. Spread half of batter in greased 2-quart glass dish.
Spread half of blueberries on batter; sprinkle with half of Nut Topping. Repeat layers with remaining batter, blueberries and Nut Topping. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In hot margarine, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until lightly browned. Add beef.
Cook, stirring until red color disappears.
Stir in lemon juice, wine, consomme, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in uncooked noodles.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Mix in sour cream; heat quickly but do not boil.
Serve at once.
Yields 8 good size servings.

title: harvey's bristol creme cake
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients as per instructions on cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
In small cup, mix Harvey's Bristol Creme liquor and instant coffee.
Swirl through cake with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla. Drop off spoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake for about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, Equal and lemon juice in medium bowl until smooth.
Gently mix in fruit.
Spoon mixture into 12 paper lined muffin cups or spread in 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Garnish with pecan halves and additional fruit.
Freeze until firm, 6 to 8 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skin with eggs for about 45 minutes.
Peel potatoes and eggs and dice into a medium size bowl.
Dice onions and add to potatoes and eggs along with sweet relish, salt, black pepper and white vinegar.
Add salad dressing last.
Mix together until well blended.
You may boil an extra egg to slice and put on top with paprika sprinkled on it.

title: mrs. nelson's cookies
directions: Mix sugar and oleo. Add eggs, then other ingredients. Bake about 8 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: hot tamales
directions: Blend in blender: onions, garlic, water and tomato sauce.
Add to ground meat with all of the ingredients except cornmeal.
Mix well. Take about 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Roll oblong, then roll in cornmeal.
Wrap in tamale papers (wet papers first so they won't be stiff), then put all the tamales in a large pot, layers in opposite directions.

title: pig in the blanket
directions: Combine all ingredients together except the tomato juice and paprika.
Heat cabbage in large pot until leaves can by removed easily.
When leaves are removed fill with hamburger mixture, and roll up and secure with a toothpick, if needed.
Put tomato juice and paprika into large pot and add the cabbage rollsl.
Cook on low to medium heat for about 2 hours or until the meat mixture in the cabbage rolls are done.
tags: head of cabbage with big leaves

title: creme de menthe squares
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Blend in flour, vanilla, salt and chocolate syrup.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then cool for one hour.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Boil jello, pineapple and water for 1 minute.
Cool and add marshmallows, cottage cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: doni's quiche
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Grate cheeses.
Crumble cooked bacon on top of cheese.
Sprinkle with onion powder, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend until smooth.
Beat eggs, milk and Bisquick together.
Pour over cheese and bacon.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes or when done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, potato chips, nuts and chocolate chips.
Form into balls; flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325°.

title: skinny ranch dip(for vegetables)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Serve with vegetables.
Makes 12 calories per tablespoon and has 0 fat.

title: sid's vegetable soup
directions: Brown stew meat in skillet in a small amount of oil.
Add to your crock-pot along with all remaining ingredients.
Cook all day (minimum of 8 hours) at low temperature.

title: mountain mama mud slide
directions: Combine and mix.
Spread over bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or so, until golden brown.
Let cool

title: yum yum brownies
directions: Grease and flour 8 X 8 X 2 inch pan.
In medium bowl, stir sugar, flour, cocoa, and salt.
Stir in corn oil.
Add eggs, one at at time, and beat well after each.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until tooth pick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in fat; add water, cover and simmer 1 hour. Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly. Pour sauce over hot pork.
Let stand 10 minutes and add green peppers, onions and pineapple chunks.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Be sure pepper and onion is just tender-crisp.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In a small saucepan, saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Add cheese and cook over low heat until melted. Stir in broccoli and rosemary. Cut top off bread. Scoop out center of bread. Serve with bread cubes and raw vegetables.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix together with mixer the egg, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla extract. Slice 1 frozen cookie roll and line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Fill in with pieces and press down. Spread cream cheese layer on top of cookie layer. Slice 2nd cookie roll and place on cream cheese mixture. Fill in with pieces as needed. Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes, until brown on outside but when shaken the center is a bit soft. Refrigerate; overnight is best. Slice and serve cold.

title: mango bread
directions: Stir all items together until just mixed.
This will make a thick, heavy mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan (5 x 9 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: stuffed roast pepper soup
directions: In large Dutch oven or soup kettle, cook ground beef with onion until the meat is brown and the onion is tender; drain.
Add bouillon cubes, tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add chopped peppers, cook, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes or just until tender. Makes 14 to 16 servings (4 quarts).

title: cocktail-sandwich ring(good hostess gift!  may be frozen)
directions: In small bowl, blend half of cheese, braunschweiger, mustard and olives; set aside.
In small bowl, blend well remaining cream cheese, tuna, onion, nuts and pepper sauce; set aside.
Spread one filling, sandwich style, between rye slice.
Spread other filling between pumpernickel slices.
Arrange sandwich upright, pressing close together and alternating fillings, in a ring around outer edge of 10-inch plate.
Decorate filled sandwich edges alternately with minced parsley and pimento strips.
Fill center of plate with parsley sprigs.
Wrap tight with plastic wrap; refrigerate up to 3 days.
Makes about 28 sandwiches.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Beat eggs until frothy and blend in mayonnaise; add all other ingredients except bread crumbs. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish. Top with buttered crumbs and bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, eggs, cinnamon, salt, ginger and nutmeg. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Lower heat to 350°; bake 35 to 40 minutes more, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts in small pieces.
Leave cut up overnight in pan.
Sift 2 cups flour over mixture.
Cream butter and sugar with eggs.
Add soda with remaining flour and buttermilk to mixture. Pour over fruit mixture; mix well.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 275°. While hot, mix 2 cups brown sugar with 1 cup orange juice and pour over cake.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Cut cheese in chunks.
Do not grate.
Place half of ingredients in blender.
Turn on high until thoroughly mixed. Remove from blender and continue process with remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased, uncovered casserole dish at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
This can be mixed a day ahead of time.

title: chicken cacciatora
directions: Slowly brown chicken in 1/4 cup hot oil.
Remove from skillet. Add onion and garlic to skillet; cook until tender, but not brown.
Combine remaining ingredients together, creating sauce. Add chicken to skillet and pour sauce over.
Cover and let simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook, uncovered, turning chicken occasionally, for another 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and sauce is thick.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
This is great with Cool Whip.

title: amy's plum pudding balls
directions: Put dates, figs and pecans through coarsest cutter of a food grinder.
Mix in diced candied cherries and bottled lemon juice. Shape into balls, using 2 teaspoons of fruit and nut mixture.
Roll balls in flaked coconut.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: brown rice
directions: Put 2 cans of soup in casserole dish.
Add 1/2 stick margarine, onion powder and rice.
Stir to mix.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes after covering dish.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add nuts, bananas and flour, then milk with soda and vanilla.
Bake in layers in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Put together with Burnt Sugar Icing or whatever icing preferred.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and flour until thick, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Mix together melted margarine and powdered sugar.
Put into baked pie shell (9-inch). Top this with sliced strawberries; them pour warm Jell-O mixture over this.
Chill.
When cool and set, top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Makes 1 large pie.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients and stir until mixed well. Pour in unbaked pie shell and cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until it shakes like jello in the center and is light brown.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crumbs over margarine and pat in crust.
Layer in order given: margarine, crumbs, coconut, nuts and morsels and pour Eagle Brand milk over all. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, until chocolate is melted and bubbly.

title: meat pie roma
directions: Brown meat, add green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in sauce mix, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Line with biscuits.
Press together to seal. Pour in 1/2 meat mixture.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining meat and top with Mozzarella cheese in lattice-work fashion.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lima-broccoli casserole
directions: Place vegetables and soups into greased casserole dish.
Melt the oleo and add Rice Krispies.
Saute together, then add to top of casserole (or sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ellie's chicken
directions: Skin the chicken pieces; dip in butter or margarine.
Roll in crushed seasoned stuffing mix.
Brown in butter or margarine; put in low baking dish.
Pour chicken broth until an inch high.
Cover with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in 13 x 9-inch pan in order listed and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly bread
directions: Heat
oven
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients
except preserves.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix above ingredients and put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sleigh bells punch
directions: Mix all together and serve. Serves 25.

title: ham and cheese biscuit sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk, ham and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Turn onto surface well-floured with baking mix.
Gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Knead 10 times.
Pat or roll dough into ten 10-inch strips.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush strips with margarine.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Make Rice-A-Roni according to package.
Boil the chicken breasts 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Shred chicken and set aside.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Rinse and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together the soup, shredded Jack cheese, 1/2 package taco cheese, corn, sour cream, salsa, green chilies (chopped), chili powder and shredded chicken.
Stir in noodles. Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add cooked Rice-A-Roni to chicken mixture and pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining taco cheese over top of casserole.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes or until top is bubbly and brown.

title: turketti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Place meat, pimento and green pepper in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add all other ingredients, reserving 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Mix lightly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour in graham cracker crust.
Let set, then freeze.
Serve frozen with Dream Whip.
(I have used lemon instead of lime juice.)

title: ham puffs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Stir in milk, egg yolks and crumbs. Fold in egg whites. Fill 6 greased 6-ounce custard cups. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set. Turn out on plates; top with Mushroom Sauce.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Add ingredients in order. Stir as you add them.

title: butter balls
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small balls on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: williamsburg squash
directions: Cook and mash squash or add frozen squash.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon, salt and milk together.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar and set to about jelled.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Set until jelled in refrigerator a day ahead.

title: sugar pecans
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, water and cinnamon. Cook to a firm soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add pecans. Stir to coat all pecans. Pour on wax paper and let stand until cool. Break apart. Makes a good sweet treat.

title: pina colada ice cream
directions: In large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, cream of coconut and rum or flavoring.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: vodka carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into strips.
Melt butter over medium heat and saute carrots 2 to 3 minutes.
Add onions and cinnamon. Stir 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add vodka.
Stir well.
Cover and cook over low heat (simmer) for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bean and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat skillet; heat oil.
Add onion, carrots, broccoli, red pepper and garlic; stir-fry.
Add beans, black pepper, paprika and Mrs. Dash to vegetables.
Add water and bouillon.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pina colada mold
directions: Blend all ingredients except the Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Freeze until 1/2 hour before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand and partially cool. Melt yeast in warm water and add liquified yeast to above.
Add butter, molasses or honey and salt to oats and yeast.
Add 2 cups flour and stir well.
Add 2 more cups of flour which may be difficult but will gradually blend in.
Add last 2 cups of flour, a little at a time, while kneading well until dough is smooth and elastic (takes about 15 minutes).

title: frosted olives
directions: Drain and pat dry olives; mold cream cheese around olives and roll in ground pecans.
Cut in half.
These are very good and are pretty on a tray, especially at Christmas.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: In bowl, combine Crisco, egg, brown sugar, milk and vanilla. Mix together oatmeal, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Combine with Crisco mixture. Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop teaspoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse in cold water.
Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 5 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
May be stored in freezer and baked as needed.

title: polish dessert
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend margarine, flour and nuts; spread in bottom of pan.
Cook for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan.
Beat together the cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on crust.
Mix milk with chocolate pudding and vanilla pudding in separate bowls.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate for a few hours before serving in squares.
This freezes well if you want to make ahead.
Just defrost in refrigerator before serving.

title: hodge-podge
directions: Brown meats; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients along with water or tomato juice--enough to achieve desired thickness. May also add any other ingredients which seem compatible. Simmer to blend flavors. Makes around four quarts, depending.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Soak rice for 1 hour in warm water to cover.
Put rice in large pot with cream and a dash of salt.
Bring to boil, stirring often.
Cook slow for 15 minutes.
While rice is cooking, beat eggs in a bowl; add sugar and vanilla.
Set aside.
Remove pot from stove when rice is done and add egg mixture.
Return to heat and bring to a wee boil.
Pour into a large bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Process a little at a time and slowly add remaining can of cream soup.
Blend until smooth.
Add slowly to the cooked rice and blend in additional milk to consistency of your choice.

title: chow chow relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 4 to 6 hours in cool place.
Drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add vegetables, simmering 10 minutes more.
Bring mixture to a boil; pack into pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch space.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: joyce's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Add flour and salt and mix well.
Add oats, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut in pieces.
Place in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Add other ingredients.
Toss to coat. Cover.
Cook on 100% power 12 to 15 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir before serving.

title: caramel pear salad
directions: Combine the pears, pecans, cherries, and lemon juice.
Gently stir to mix well.
Pour the pear mixture into a shallow dish. Spoon the sour cream evenly over the top. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or until chilled and brown sugar has dissolved into the sour cream.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer noodles 3 at a time with other ingredients.
Put Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese starts to melt. Let cool slightly.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and creamy and lemon color.
Continue beating; add milk, oil and dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Fry on hot grid iron or skillet and serve with syrup or jelly.

title: manicotti
directions: Crepes: Stir flour, water and salt until smooth. Beat in 4 eggs one at a time. Pour batter into 5 to 6-inch greased pan (do not brown).

title: vanilla yogurt dip
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 1 hour or overnight.

title: healthy joes
directions: Spray skillet with Pam and brown meat and onions.
Add tomato sauce, salsa and brown sugar.
Lower heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into Pyrex dish (loaf style) and chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over first layer, spreading evenly.
Cover with remaining jello mixture.
Chill.
Cut into squares and serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with dab of sour cream and whole strawberry.
This may also be used as a dessert.

title: deviled ham and cream cheese
directions: Mix ham and cheese together.
Spread on bread.
Broil in hot oven.
Cut in strips.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except chocolate syrup.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter into separate bowl; stir in 1/4 cup chocolate syrup.
Spoon batter alternately into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back. Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: dry bean soup (lentil)
directions: Wash beans and soak for an hour in warm water.
Drain beans and cook beans and ham in above ingredients for 2 hours.
Melt lard, shortening or margarine (2 tablespoons).
Add 2 tablespoons flour.
Brown.
Add a little to soup; spoon out beans and put to browned flour.
Bring to boil; add soup to get the right consistency.
Take out ham bone and noodles to soup.
Eat creamed beans with ham.
Leftover ham makes delicious cold cuts.
Instead of ham, a pork roast or spareribs can be used.
You might substitute beans with lentils.

title: easy hamburger stroganoff(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Saute minced onion in butter.
Add beef; brown slightly.
Add flour, seasonings, soups and noodles; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add sour cream; mix carefully.

title: apricot brandy cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Mix sour cream, apricot brandy and all extracts together.
Now alternately add sour cream mixture and flour mixture into creamed butter and sugar mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured angel food cake pan. Bake at 325°
for 70 minutes, or until done.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Spoon into paper-lined or buttered muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: zucchini jack casserole
directions: Slice zucchini crosswise, 1/4-inch thick, about 7 cups.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt, baking powder and flour until smooth.
Stir in parsley, garlic, onion, green chilies, cheese and zucchini.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Toss croutons in melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until set in center and squash is tender.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: my mom's date bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well. Add flour mixture (put salt and baking powder in flour) a little at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add nuts and dates; blend well.
Put in greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (may vary).
When done, cut in bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: broil special
directions: Place the temperature of the oven at broil.
Place broil in an aluminum pan and slice about 10 slits into it.
First season it with the onion, garlic and seasoned salt on top and under.
Now poke holes into the broil with a fork.
Then take a 1/4 to 1/2 cup of soy sauce and a 1/2 cup of melted butter and marinate the London Broil.
Flip it once or twice so the seasoning gets through the whole steak.
Let the steak set for about 15 to 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain asparagus; save liquid.
Blend flour, butter, asparagus liquid, salt and water.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Line a 1 1/2-quart casserole with bread crumbs; reserve some for top.
Place asparagus, almonds, cheese and eggs in layers.
Pour sauce over this.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake until brown.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sugar donuts
directions: Beat together the sugar, eggs, cream, milk and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Cover top with waxed paper.
Fry in shortening as any other donut.

title: hot 'n easy snack
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch squares.
Spread tops with mayonnaise and cover with cheese.
Brown in 450° oven.
Great to serve to crowd after a game.

title: asparagus toast
directions: Drain the liquid from the can of asparagus and mix with 1 teaspoon of cornstarch.
Place asparagus in saucepan with liquid mixture and heat until hot and slightly thickened.
Place scoop of asparagus mixture on the toast with bacon bits and small dot of oleomargarine.
Place under broiler until oleomargarine melts.

title: quick fix banana nut bread
directions: In a blender, put banana(s), shortening, egg, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into a mixing bowl; gradually add flour.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
It is best if you let set for 15 to 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
It is done when top is dry and cracked.
Remove from pan onto a cooling rack.
Let cool before cutting.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain meat on paper towel.
Mix all ingredients and simmer on top of stove until gravy gets a little thick.
Put in casserole dish.
Put 10 Butter-Me-Not biscuits on top. Cook as directed for biscuits to get done.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and egg in bowl; beat until light. Carefully blend in combined flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Turn mixture into an ungreased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Serve warm or cold topped with whipped cream or ice cream. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: california avocado party dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes approximately 4 cups of avocado guacamole dip.
Serve with crunchy tortilla or corn chips.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add rhubarb.
Mix well.
Pour in pie and add top.
Bake at 325° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: For shells, combine cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add flour. Put dough in refrigerator for 1 hour, then shape dough into small balls. Press and shape them into shells in miniature muffin tins. Bake shells for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Cook in crock pot on low all day or high for 4-6 hours, or simmer on stove for 2 hours.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Melt chips.
Beat egg yolks and add to chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add to mixture.
Beat whipped cream and add to mixture.
Cut or tear cake in pieces.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 of the pieces.
Pour 1/2 of chocolate mixture over that and repeat.

title: elbow room marinade
directions: Combine first three ingredients in electric blender and process at high speed until smooth (one minute).
Stir in gravy coloring and Beau Monde.

title: shanghai roasted chicken wings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together and stir.
Wash and disjoint fresh chicken wings.
Fry them in 350° oil for about 5 to 8 minutes or until a crunchy brown.
Or roast them in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until a golden brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Add salt, flour, shortening and water in bowl and mix well.
Work flour until easy to handle. Roll dough thin.
Cut into squares and drop into boiling chicken broth.

title: harvest pumpkin bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Beat in oil. Toss together the flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.

Add dry ingredients and walnuts to pumpkin mixture, stirring until just combined; be careful not to overmix. Grease and flour two 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans or one 9-inch tube pan; fill with batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Let stand about 15 minutes.
Turn out on cooling rack.

title: chicken and rice valencia
directions: Saute chicken pieces 1 minute in hot olive oil in Dutch oven. Add onion, pepper, tomatoes, bay leaf, water, saffron and olives. Cover and cook over low heat about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
About 25 minutes before chicken is done, prepare rice as directed on package.
Just before serving, add celery and celery leaves.
Serve chicken on rice and spoon sauce on top.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve ice cream in hot Jell-O mixture.
Add frozen strawberries, thawed, and angel food cake, broken.
Place broken cake in bottom of dish.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and brown sugar; add flour and nuts.
Blend until crumbly.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture. Press remainder into greased 8-inch square pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar; beat egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over layer in pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs. Bake 25 minutes.
Refrigerate and cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: loretta's barbecue hash
directions: Cook beef covered with water until tender.
Save 2 cups of cooking liquid.
Let meat cool, then grind, shred or chop.
Place in Dutch oven or heavy pot.
Add all the other ingredients and cook over low heat until peppers and potatoes are tender, about 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Good for a crowd or two teenage boys.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 30 minutes at 350° in a greased pan.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Mix eggs, salt, pepper, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside. Roll out rolls on pizza pan or cookie sheet, pressing cracks together.

title: chinese cabbage slaw
directions: Crumble dry noodles over the slaw mix.
Add green onions, diced up small.
Set in refrigerator while preparing remainder of ingredients.
Put flavor packet from Ramen noodles in a small saucepan.
Add vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook until sugar dissolves; set aside to cool.
In a small skillet, melt margarine.
Add sliced almonds; heat on low heat until the almonds are toasted (lightly browned).
Set aside to cool.
Before serving, combine the slaw mixture, the vinegar mixture and the almonds.
Toss lightly.

title: diane's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add egg yolks, water and milk.
Cook until thick.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Brown.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Put frozen lemonade concentrate in blender.
Fill can with 7-Up and add to lemonade in blender.
Add a few ice cubes and blend on high until slushy.
Add frozen strawberries.
Blend on high until slushy.
Pour into punch bowl and add 1 (2 liter) size 7-Up.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix and press down a layer of oatmeal mixture in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling and top with remaining oatmeal lightly.
Bake until brown.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding sugar gradually.
Add well-beaten egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to butter mixture.
Roll into balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400°.

title: rye boat dip
directions: Mix and
chill.
Make a boat out of a loaf of rye bread and fill with dip.
Use rye bread to dip with.

title: meat balls(farm city day 1989)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into balls and brown in skillet.
Simmer in 2 cups beef bouillon until ready to serve. Use a crock-pot if desired.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, beating until sugar and butter are completely dissolved.

title: rhubarb cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium size saucepan.
Stir in rhubarb, pie filling and allspice.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Let boil 1 minute until thickened. Remove from heat.
Cool until lukewarm.

title: lemon frosting
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour and beat again.
Have butter at room temperature and add butter; beat again.
Add reserved lemon juice and rind.
Stir in; do not beat.
Cook in a double boiler until frosting thickens.
Stir frequently.
Let cool.

title: bathtub fingerpaint
directions: Place cornstarch in a medium saucepan.
Add water a little at a time.
Stir until water and cornstarch are mixed well.
Cook this mixture over low to medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Stir continuously while cooking.
Mixture usually thickens in 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add powder and dishwashing liquid.
Stir until mixed.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake 1/4 hour more.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and milk.
Season with vanilla.
Bake in unbaked crust.
This makes 2 pies.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain fruits; boil juice and melt jello.
Cream the cream cheese with Coke, starting with a little, then gradually adding the rest.
Add cooled jello and nuts.
Chill.

title: punch
directions: Mix orange juice and 3 cans of water.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Drink after thawing partially.
Should still be slushy.

title: hot russian tea
directions: Stir all together and store in jars.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons for each cup.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved.

title: hotsie-totsie
directions: Drain peppers; cut into pieces.
Put in pie pan (9 or 10-inch buttered).
Mix eggs to blend.
Add milk.
Sprinkle cheese over peppers.
Pour on eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm or hot with crackers.

title: blueberries 'n' cream squares
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter well (reserve 1/2 cup for topping). Press into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill.

title: pork chop and potato dinner
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and lay in bottom of 13 x 9-inch (or larger) baking pan.
Salt and pepper pork chops and lay on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle flour over top of pork chops, then pour in enough milk to completely cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done you have pork chops, potatoes and gravy.

title: deluxe lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together first three ingredients until mixture clings.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or dish. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.

title: aloha casserole
directions: Saute turkey, chicken or tuna in butter.
Add in celery, onion, soup and water.
Then add pineapple, nuts and noodles.
Put all ingredients in buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh greens with honey jalapeno dressing
directions: Peel orange; slice thinly.
Quarter each slice.
Put greens, orange pieces and almonds in bowl; drizzle with dressing and toss. Serve immediately.

title: eddy's oatmeal patties
directions: Put everything in blender except oats and bread crumbs; whiz it up, including onion.
Measure patties by tablespoonful and fry in hot skillet.
Cover with Mushroom Gravy.

title: fat-free jalapeno frittata
directions: Wash and remove stems from the jalapenos.
Chop jalapenos in either a food processor or blender.
Place chopped jalapenos in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Be sure the bottom of the dish is completely covered.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, oleo and sugar; spread over 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix cream cheese (softened), 1/2 cup sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add sugar and cornstarch mixture gradually.
Add vanilla. Pile on pie and seal edges of crust with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: my favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, saving chocolate chips for last.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on gray cookie sheet.
(The gray cookie sheet prevents cookies from burning on the bottom.) Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes several dozen.

title: aunt doll's five-pound fudge
directions: Over medium high heat boil first 3 ingredients for 8 minutes until all crystals are gone. Melt next 2 ingredients in microwave for 4 minutes. Stir for 2 minutes and add nuts. Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring until well blended and chocolate is completely melted. Pour into 2 well buttered 9 x 13 inch pans. In about 30 minutes cut into small squares.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Put mixture of the first 3 ingredients in crock jar to sour. When mixture is as sour as you like, take 2 cups of mixture and add the sugar, salt and baking powder. Pour mixture into a 6-inch skillet and bake in a 350° oven for 21 minutes. After bread has cooked 21 minutes, grease top of bread with oleo, place under broiler and brown. It will not brown like any other bread.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Slice strawberries into large bowl.
Add peaches and pineapple including juice.
Slice bananas and add.
Stir gently to coat bananas.
Drain juice off (will be approximately 1 cup).
Combine juice and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth (wire whip works best). Pour over fruit.
Gently mix.

title: pudding pops
directions: Measure peanut butter into small bowl.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add instant pudding mix.
Spoon into cups and put stick in.
Cover with plastic and put in freezer for 2 hours.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: In a bowl, combine the biscuit mix, Parmesan cheese, pepper and eggs just until blended.
Add the zucchini; mix well.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Drop batter by about 1/3 cupfuls into skillet; press lightly to flatten.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes on each side.
Yield: 5 pancakes.

title: "dirt cake" recipe
directions: Remove white filling from Oreo cookies.
Place cookies in a Ziploc bag, seal and crush using a rolling pin.
Set aside.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and turn into casserole dish.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in jello until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Put in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Delicious.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in melted butter.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and add onion.
Add all cans; simmer.
Layer as follows in a 9 x 13-inch dish:
6 tortillas, meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers; top with cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into shell.
Chill.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake one hour at 350° or until done.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut tops off and clean out seeds.
Be careful not to break peppers. Mix hamburger, rice, salt, pepper, eggs and chopped onion. Fill peppers as full as possible with the meat mixture.
Place in greased baking pan, open end up.
Cover with tomato sauce. Cover pan with tight fitting lid. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until hamburger is done.

title: eggnog quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, eggnog, margarine, rum extract and vanilla; blend well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 1 (16 slice) loaf or can be baked in two 5 3/4 x 3 1/4-inch loaf pans, greased on bottoms only.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Place nuts, cherries, pineapple and dates into a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Put orange juice in a saucepan over low heat or boiling water and add marshmallows.
Stir until all marshmallows are melted and sauce is smooth.
Crush crackers (or put in blender) or use graham cracker crumbs.
Pour juice and marshmallow mixture over crackers; stir until they are mixed well, all crumbs must be moistened.
Mix crumb mixture with the fruits and mix well.
Line a tube pan with wax paper, make sure that the tube pan is completely covered with wax paper inside.
Pack the fruit cake mixture down into the tube pan, pressing down good as you put in the mixture.
Cover with wrapping paper or put in an airtight container.
Put in refrigerator for 5 hours at least before slicing to serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes or so.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients at low speed in blender.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan over low heat.
Mix in 2 cups brown sugar until melted.
Cool slightly.
Beat in 2 well-beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and baking powder very well, then add to brown sugar and egg mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped walnuts and coconut.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: snowflake salad
directions: Combine lemon jello with hot water, stirring until jello is dissolved, then add pineapple juice.
Cool until consistency of syrup.
Whip and add cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and nuts. Mix and fold in whipped cream or commercial substitute.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Serve on lettuce.

title: squash casserole 1
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mash squash and onion. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake 40 minutes at 370° or until firm.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Pierce sweet potatoes with a fork.
Bake in 400° oven for 55 to 65 minutes, or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Remove pulp from potatoes, keeping the skins intact.
In a bowl, combine pulp with pineapple juice, orange juice, butter and salt.
Refill potato shells; place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sherry beef
directions: Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together, except chocolate chips.
Beat 2 minutes. Stir in chips.
Spray with Pam and flour a funnel cake pan or Bundt pan.
Pour mixture in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cool 30 minutes and dump from pan.

title: roast beef salad
directions: Toss all together and add dressing.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all eggs in large bowl or blender.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam (or whatever you use).
Pour in mixed eggs, browned sausage and cheese.
Add butter, salt and pepper, stir around.
Bake around 40 minutes (until firm).

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese in order given.
Pour half the batter into a hot, well-greased iron skillet.
Sprinkle half the cheese over the batter.
Add remaining mixture and top with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Boil together the first three ingredients for 3 minutes.
Mix jello and water and add to pineapple mixture.
When it starts to congeal add shredded cheese.
Add nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
This is delicious.
Makes a big salad.
Can be made the day before it is served.

title: chicken swiss crisscross
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press 2 rectangles into bottom and 1/4-inch up sides of ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or bake for 30 minutes and then freeze. When ready to use; completely thaw and then bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin and cool.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Set overnight.

title: chicken and pineapple
directions: Mix soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, pineapple juice, cornstarch and salt.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple in a saucepan and bring to boil. Stir in jello until well-dissolved.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in nuts and cheese.
Fold in whipped cream and chill until set.

title: spiced tea sugar free
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use one heaping teaspoonful in cup of hot water.
Stir well.

title: fruit slaw
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons pineapple juice with oil, sweetener, lemon juice and ginger. Mix well.

title: cheeseburger upside down pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil in skillet.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Cook a little longer, Stirring until thickened.
Pour into a 8 X 8 X 2 inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Shape each biscuit into a 4 inch stick.
Arrange over cheese.
Bake in hot oven at 425 for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: chili stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake or microwave potatoes until tender.
Heat chili according to package directions.
Slice open hot potatoes; fluff with fork. Top with chili, cheese, sour cream and green onions.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Mix soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce together.
Brown pork chops.
Place in casserole dish and pour soup mixture over chops.
Slice onion thinly over dish and cook, covered, in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute ground beef with next four ingredients in skillet until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for one hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach pizza
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour, melted margarine, brown sugar and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat out like a pizza crust.
Cook 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool.
Whip cream cheese with powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread this on cool crust.
Cook in saucepan until thick, then add 13 ounce box peach jello and cool.
Add 4 cups sliced peaches.
Drain fruit well before adding.
Pour mixture over cream cheese.
Let chill overnight.

title: how to make buttermilk
directions: Ever start a recipe calling for buttermilk and you didn't have or maybe never buy it?
Well, make it.

title: pepper steak italian style
directions: Cut peppers into thin strips.
In large skillet, cook peppers, onion and garlic in hot oil for about 4 minutes.
Remove; keep warm.
Place meat in same skillet (add more oil if necessary). Add salt and pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat.
Transfer to a platter; keep warm.
Carefully add the beef broth, oregano and basil to skillet.
Bring to boiling.
Boil gently, uncovered, over medium heat for 3 minutes, or until broth is reduced to 1/3 cup.
Stir in the pepper and tomato mixture.
Add the meat.
Spoon onto platter.
Serves 4.

title: nacho dip
directions: Saute meat with onion.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Heat until melted.
Use mild or hot chilies and sauce, according to your taste.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: wassail
directions: Tie cloves & cinnamon stick together & put in cheese cloth. Mix all ingredients together in a big pot & place cheese cloth in it.
Bring all to a boil & reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Take cheese cloth out & sip & enjoy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into measuring cup.
Add water to juice to measure 2 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce to jello mixture and stir until dissolved.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until cool (approximately 15 minutes).
Add celery, pineapple and pecans. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese squares
directions: Cut into cake mix 1 egg and margarine (will be lumpy).
Spread this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat together powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over cake mixture in pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
It will be bubbly and rise in the middle.
Let cool and cut into desired size squares.

title: melt in your mouth cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Spread berries on bottom and sprinkle with nuts and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Beat eggs; add one cup of sugar gradually.
Beat until well mixed.
Add flour, butter and shortening.
Beat well and pour over berries.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: father's day biscuits
directions: Melt butter in biscuit pan.
Use enough flour to mix with the buttermilk to make dough.
Stir with fork just until moistened. Too much stirring makes the biscuits tough.
Gather dough together with hands and knead 3 to 4 times.
Pat or roll out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
(A back and forth rolling motion makes the biscuits tough.)
Cut into biscuits with a 2 to 3-inch biscuit cutter or top of a glass that's been dipped into flour.
(Do not twist the cutter, the biscuits won't rise as high.) Dip biscuits into butter in the pan.
Turn each biscuit over so the buttered side is up.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425° or until golden brown on top.
Serve with a big smile and a big hug to your favorite guy for Father's Day!

title: fruit tea punch
directions: Make a syrup of 2 cups of sugar and 1 cup of water.
Add tea, fruit juices and enough water to make 1 1/2 gallons.
Stir in strawberries and ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 50 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan. Mix together ingredients; pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snack oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers), stir and let sit for 2 to 5 minutes.
Add oyster crackers, mix until fully coated.
Spray cookie sheet pan with oil spray.
Lay crackers in one layer.
Cook in oven at 250° for 15-20 minutes.

title: ground beef-mushroom quiche
directions: May substitute sausage for ground beef.
Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch and pepper together.
Add all other ingredients to mixture and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: angel hair toss
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Stir-fry for 1 minute the garlic and onions.
Stir in tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper; cook for 2 minutes.
Toss with cooked angel hair.

title: tiramisu(pick me up)
directions: Whip the heavy cream.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks, sugar and lemon rind.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese and egg mixture and mix well; fold in whipped cream.

title: artichoke pape'
directions: In saucepan, mix oil and butter with basil, garlic, peppers and herbs.
Cook until garlic is half done.
Add olives and pepperoncinis.
Cook for 1 minute.

title: mini-cal strawberry torte
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk powder, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Combine oil, water and vanilla, beating with a wire whisk.
Stir liquid into flour mixture until dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat the egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed with an electric mixer until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into cake batter.
Spoon batter into a 9-inch spring-form pan that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove cake from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Return cooled cake to reassembled pan.
Set aside 6 strawberries.
Cut in half enough strawberries to make a ring around the cake.
Arrange cut sides against the pan.
Stand remaining berries on top of the cake.
Pour topping over the berries.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Transfer cake to serving plate.
Cut the reserved strawberries in half and arrange on top of the cake. Garnish the plate with sprigs of fresh mint.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs well.
Blend in bananas and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda, which have been mixed together alternately with sour milk only until well combined.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 casseroles.
Bake 1 and freeze 1 for later.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: In double boiler, add gelatine, 2 tablespoons of sugar, salt, milk and chocolate; stir until chocolate melts.
Beat until blended.
In another bowl, beat egg yolks and 2 teaspoons of sugar. Stir in a little chocolate and mix.
Add back into double boiler, stirring until thickened.
Cool.
Stir in vanilla after cooled. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar; beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Place in cooked pie shell.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sauce. Stir in pecans. Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes. Stir while baking and taste test.

title: potatoes and pork chops
directions: Slice potatoes; chop onion.
Season pork chops; brown in frypan.
Melt butter; add flour and blend well.
Add milk slowly. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Alternately place potatoes, onion, cream sauce and pork chops in a greased casserole.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°, until tender. Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; add other ingredients.
Bake 1-1/2 hours at 350 degrees in well-greased bundt pan.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover; cook at 300° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sunflower pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour loaf pan.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Mix pumpkin, oil, sunflower seeds and walnuts in large bowl.
Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture (batter will be thick).
Bake about 55 minutes.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: Refrigerate fruit for 2 hours.
Grease and flour rolling board.
Take one biscuit at a time and roll out large enough to hold fruit.
Place fruit in center of biscuit and fold over.
Take a fork and press edges together.
Put just enough shortening in skillet to barely cover bottom.
Add shortening as needed.
As soon as shortening starts to melt, reduce heat to low.
Place pies in skillet and slowly fry to allow biscuit enough time to get done.
Flip pies easily.
Cook until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes and serve.

title: adelaide's pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased dish.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool completely.

title: miracle fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and salt in 4-quart mixing bowl. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes. Stir until well blended.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 or 7 minutes or until mixture boils and forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add chocolate pieces and stir until melted.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate several hours until firm.
Cut into squares.
Top each square with walnut halves.
Makes 72 squares.

title: olive rice casserole
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Melt butter and blend in flour. Add milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce and thyme until thickens. Blend in cheese and stir over low heat until melted.
Stir in rice and olives.
Layer mixture with thin slices of tomatoes in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Cut chicken into chunks and place in a large casserole.
Place cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken and cheese.
Mix stuffing with melted butter, water and egg. Spoon over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° in oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, combine the last 4 ingredients.
Mix second mixture with the first.
Stir well.
Bake in loaf or tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: plantation pride cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Melt butter with buttermilk or sour milk.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine brown sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
(With electric mixer, use a low speed.)
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured on bottom.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Spread with topping.
Broil, watching carefully, until bubbly and golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in a Pam sprayed loaf pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups whipped cream.
Blend well. Mix in cherries, sugar and nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with remaining whipped cream.
Freeze 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli & chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in baking dish.
Put broccoli on top of chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice together.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Put cheese on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: white chip island blondies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Beat sugar, butter and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels, nuts and coconut.
Press into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cranberry oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg and mix well.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls the size of a walnut. Place in a flat pan, only 1 layer to each pan.

title: lucious chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Remove from heat and add sugar, milk, egg whites and vanilla; mix well.
Place bowl in ice and water.
Beat with electric mixer until icing is of right consistency to spread.

title: sheet cookies
directions: Put the raisins in the 2 cups water; cook down to 1 cup juice. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar icing while hot, then cut into bars.

title: caraway green beans
directions: Saute bacon and onions; add green beans and caraway seed. Simmer 1 hour on top of stove.
Pour off all juice except 1/4 cup. Add mushroom soup, cheese, water chestnuts and pepper; place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes. This can be prepared the day before.
It can also be frozen. Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked lamb ring
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; pack in a greased mold (8-inch).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over apples that have been layered in a baking dish.
Bake on low heat until apples are done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 bread pans.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla to the eggs. Beat until thick.
Add the zucchini.
Sift in the flour and the cinnamon.
Add the walnuts or pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Put one stick oleo in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Mix other ingredients.
Then pour 1/2 of oleo into mixture.
Bake at 325° until done.
You can use muffin pans.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: (Wear plastic gloves.)
Rinse jalapenos and slit to remove seeds.
Stuff with slices of each kind of cheese.
Wrap sausage around outside of jalapeno, completely covering.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn over.
Bake 15 minutes more, then broil to brown if necessary.

title: fettucini with shrimp
directions: Heat oil; add shrimp and saute 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
In same pan, saute onions, garlic, tomatoes and pepper 1 to 2 minutes.
Add wine and cook over low heat 2 to 3 minutes. Combine cornstarch and yogurt; add to skillet.
Add basil.
Return shrimp to skillet; cook 3 to 4 minutes until mixture is thickened. To serve, place 1/2 cup fettucini on plates; top with shrimp mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: boiled crawfish
directions: In a large tub or ice chest, cover crawfish with fresh water to purge them, about 15 minutes.
Drain water and repeat.
Fill a 40-quart pot 2/3 full of water and place on burner to boil.
