Add crab boil, onions and lemons and simmer the mixture once the water comes to a boil.
Add crawfish and watch closely. When water first begins to come to a boil, time for 5 minutes and turn off the heat.
Put the ice on top to stop cooking process and wait for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Refrigerate overnight. Toss with salad before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put water on to boil.
Add jello, sugar and gelatine which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Stir well and let set to thicken as you would for any other salad base, then add other ingredients.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add shredded apple and the pecans.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, milk, oil, lemon juice, vanilla, lemon peel and the egg.
Stir well and add to flour mixture.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon into 12 paper-lined muffin cups and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: juliana's party cake
directions: Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan. In large bowl combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Add frosting and sour cream; mix well.
Spread batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 42 to 52 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: old fashioned homemade soup
directions: Cook beef until tender in 2-quarts of water.
Add remaining ingredients; cook slowly until all vegetables are tender.
More tomatoes may be added, if desired.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat with onion; drain.
Combine with rest of ingredients (less Doritos).
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Doritos.

title: norma's broiled crab meltaways
directions: Halve muffins; cut each half into quarters.
If using mini bagels, just separate halves.
Arrange pieces on cookie sheets. Drain and rinse crab meat.
Mix all ingredients and spread on muffins or bagels.
Freeze thoroughly.
Can keep for weeks or months.
When ready to serve, broil until bubbly and slightly browned (3 to 5 minutes).

title: microwave nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips in microwave-safe plate.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on chips, then Monterey cheese on Cheddar cheese. Microwave approximately 2 minutes until melted and bubbly.
Great with Pace picante sauce spread on top.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Mix lime jello and hot water.
Mix and let cool.
Then add ginger ale and let start to set, then add pineapple, marshmallows, celery and chopped nuts.
Let stand until firm but not set.
Then add cream or topping, whipped (no sugar).
Mix well together.
Let stand overnight.
If put in mold, do not put mold in hot water to unmold.

title: sausage-cheese treats
directions: Note: You can substitute 2 boxes frozen spinach, thawed and drained, for the sausage.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Put on floured board.
Roll out to size needed.
Place in pie pan.
Bake at 375° until done, about 15 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all at once.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add rest.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pink salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add Jell-O, a little at a time; mix real good.
Mix in cottage cheese, then pineapple, then marshmallows, then nuts or coconut.
Put Saran Wrap over bowl; let set in refrigerator.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well. Bake in loaf pan until golden brown, about 35 minutes, at 350°.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook onion in margarine until transparent.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli in water until just tender.
Do not drain.
Cool.
Cut broccoli into pieces.
Add onion, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add rice. Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spray pan with cooking ease.
Bake at 325° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Slice green onions using tops as well.
Mix with green chiles, soup, chicken and sour cream in saucepan and heat.
Fry tortillas in oil just 5 to 10 seconds.
Do not let them get crisp, drain on paper towels.
Put small amount sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fill and roll tortillas, layer sauce, tortillas, cheese and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, picante sauce and extra sour cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare firm, tart apples by peeling and slicing as you would for a regular pie. Arrange in large pie plate. Use enough apples to fill.

title: jewelry dough
directions: Measure and mix all ingredients except the water in a mixing bowl.
Add warm water slowly to make a very stiff dough.
If you add a little too much water, sprinkle the mixture with a little flour.
Form into jewelry; let dry and paint with tempera paints.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix juice, soy sauce, sugar, Tabasco sauce, lemon juice and hoisin sauce.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes on each side or until liquid has thickened and chicken wings are browned.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs.

Bake 1/2 of the prepared cake batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes. Melt margarine with caramels and milk in top of double boiler. Remove from heat and cool slightly before drizzling over top of cake layer. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Spoon remaining batter over caramel mixture and bake an additional 25 minutes at the same temperature.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: While hot, cut baked potatoes in half. Do not rip skins.
Whip potatoes.
Add oleo and beat in milk. Stir in onion, salt, pepper and grated cheese. Spoon back into shells (will usually fill 7). Sprinkle with more grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
These potatoes can be kept in warm oven until serving time. Cover with foil after baking.

title: no fail caramel icing
directions: Cook until desired consistency.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in bottom of greased casserole dish. Add soup and milk; stir well.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add oleo, then bread crumbs.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes, until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together.
(Will be too stiff to mix thoroughly.)
Put stick of margarine on top.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Blend in nuts.
Pour into waxed paper lined bread pan (8 x 4 x 3-inch).
Chill and serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine sugar, milk and cream cheese; beat until smooth. Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Prepare whipped topping mix according to directions; spread over pecans. Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry chip cake
directions: Beat the eggs well and add oil, water and extract.
Beat at high speed, a little to mix, then add dry jello and cake mix. Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Pour in well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake as directed on package at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and split in 2 layers.

title: chicken skillet italiano
directions: Place chicken and mushrooms in shallow dish and cover with dressing.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
Drain and reserve marinade. In large skillet, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add chicken and mushrooms and cook covered over medium heat until chicken is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomato and reserved marinade.
Cook and stir until zucchini is tender. Remove from heat; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 2 minutes.
Serve.
Makes 4 servings at 265 calories each.

title: gallemore gazpacho soup
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and set overnight.
Next day, add to soup the tomatoes, cucumbers and avocados.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
This entire recipe may be halved with excellent results.
It tastes even better the day after!

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix last 3 ingredients and mix well.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: winter soup
directions: Put vegetables in 2-quart saucepan.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.

title: anti-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Chop meats, cheese and vegetables.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir before serving.
Use a large bowl. Makes a lot.
Keeps 1 week in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the sugar and milk.
Stir while cooking to soft ball stage, 236°.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; blend well.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until this begins to thicken.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut each wiener in 4 or 5 pieces.
Combine all ingredients except wiener pieces in a pan; heat and stir until combined; add wiener pieces.
Heat through and serve.

title: corn and biscuit stuffing
directions: Place crumbled biscuits and corn bread in medium size bowl. On low heat, saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Add to the crumbs and seasoning. Stir in eggs and chicken broth. Mix well. Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until nicely brown.

title: applesauce spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease small square pan.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: frozen grape salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, salad dressing and pineapple syrup; mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in paper lined muffin tins and freeze.
Next day place in freezer bags and return to freezer.
Thaw for 20 to 30 minutes prior to serving.
Makes 16 muffins.
Best made with Tokay grapes but seedless red grapes are okay.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a punch bowl, floating strawberries on top.

title: white trash
directions: Mix all ingredients (using the quantity you desire). Melt white almond bark. Pour into mixture and stir. Spoon helpings onto cookie sheet and let cool.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until limp. Turn into 2-quart baking dish.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: quick peach (fruit) cobbler
directions: Melt butter
in
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk; mix well.
Pour over melted butter, but do not stir.
In
a
saucepan, combine fruit and remaining sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over batter, but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: shredded yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and water; cook until syrup. Add margarine.
Shred yams into a gallon of water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Drain and wash well.
Put in Pyrex dish, 12 x 6 x 3-inch.
Pour pineapple juice over, then syrup.
Cook at 350° in oven for 35 minutes or until they are transparent.
Serves 12. For best taste, many like the potatoes baked for approximately one hour.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 separate bowls, mix flour, soda, buttermilk and oil.
Pour flour mixture into buttermilk mixture and blend well.
Drop into baking pan and bake to golden brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onion in butter and spread over ground beef.
Mix soups and pour over hamburger and onion.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie with pretzel crust(this must be done ahead...but you'll have rave reviews.)
directions: Combine the pretzels, sugar and melted butter, mixing well. Press firmly onto the bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool on a rack.

title: macaroni and cheese lite
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook pasta until barely tender.
Drain and transfer to a large bowl.

title: crispy baked onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 4 thick slices; separate into rings.
(Reserve small rings for other uses.)
Set aside.
Combine cereal and spices.
Divide in half and set aside.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir constantly until marshmallows are melted, being careful that the mixture doesn't stick or burn.
Remove from burner.
Add Rice Krispies and mix until well coated.

title: finger salad
directions: Roll out pastry on a large cookie sheet, pressing edges together.
Press firmly.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes. Cool.
Spread with cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix. Immediately sprinkle with vegetables.
Top with grated cheese. Cut into rectangles and serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut chuck steak into bite size cubes.
Shake in a bag with flour until coated.
In a pot with oil, fry meat until brown on sides, stirring occasionally.
Let cook well, then add onion, celery, carrots and potatoes to water, enough to cover vegetables. Stir thick coating from bottom.
Bring to a boil, then add salt, peppers, garlic powder, basil and parsley.
Add a little flour to thicken.
Turn heat to a simmer, cooking for 2 hours.
Dunk Italian bread and enjoy!

title: impossible chocolate pie
directions: Mix the flour, 1/2 c. margarine and powdered sugar all together; press into a 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. While it is cooling, place all of the next ingredients into a blender.
Blend the milk, eggs, sugar, flour, soft margarine, vanilla, salt and melted chocolate chips thoroughly; pour on top of the crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
The longer, the better, as it may separate otherwise.
Top with whipped cream. Note:
For Valentine's Day, the whipped topping could be colored red or small candy hearts could be sprinkled on top.

title: arizona dip
directions: *Usually found near tuna in grocery store.

title: zippy salisbury steak
directions: In a mixing bowl combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish; blend well and set aside. In another bowl, beat egg. Add bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 c. of the soup mixture. Add ground beef and mix well. Shape into patties (makes about 6). Heat oil in large skillet and brown patties. Drain oil from skillet. Combine remaining soup mixture with water and pour over patties. Cover and cook over low to medium-low heat for 10-15 minutes or until meat is cooked through.

title: buckeyes
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls and freeze until firm (about 15 minutes).
Melt chocolate with paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cube 5 slices bread.
Beat eggs and 2 cups milk; add salt and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Cube 1/2 pound sharp cheese; put on top.
Drizzle 3 tablespoons melted butter over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Not quite enough for 8 people.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until just tender.
In skillet, brown meat and onions.
Drain.
In large casserole, combine both cans of soup and water.
Add spaghetti and meat, with onions.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted. Serves 4 to 6. (If they ask you for the recipe, use Italian accent!)

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and Crisco; set aside.
Mix your liquids and beaten eggs.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat in your flour, baking powder and salt.
When well mixed, add your dates, nuts and candy pieces.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown, 8 to 12 minutes.
This dough freezes well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar, vegetable oil and zucchini and add vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg-zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and pour into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake one hour at 350° or until top springs back when lightly pressed.
"Good."

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: orange molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add mandarin oranges and let set until it is slightly thickened.
Fold in cream and sherbet; chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat and onion; set aside.
Grate cheese; set aside. Combine corn meal, soda, milk, corn, salt and peppers.
Heat a large, deep skillet.
Grease and sprinkle corn meal over bottom of skillet.
Put in half of batter, then layer meat mixture and grated cheese, then add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Beat half and half and pie filling.
Mix in large mixing bowl with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in topping and remaining ingredients; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes to soften. Store in freezer.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolk and mash in a small bowl.
Mix in other ingredients.
Fill whites with yolk mixture, heaping high.
May be piped into whites also.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Bake in slow oven at 275° for 2 hours in bread pans.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil for 2 minutes the sugar, cocoa, oleo, milk and salt at fast speed.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add oatmeal and nut meats.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix together and spread in a deep pie pan.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with large tortilla chips or large corn chips.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place hamburger and onion in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until hamburger is browned; drain. Place hamburger mixture in baking dish.
Add Tater Tots; mix well.

title: butterscotch peanut cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips over low heat.
Add peanuts and cereal.
Mix.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Blend together mayo, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Mix everything else together in large bowl.
Add sauce and chill.

title: peltier biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Roll on floured surface.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: haystack (dip)
directions: Cook and season meat.
Spread bean dip on bottom of dish. Sprinkle meat over dip.
Mix taco mix with sour cream and spread evenly over meat.
Spread avocado dip over taco mix.
Chop onions, tomatoes and olives.
Sprinkle over mixture and top with grated cheese.
Serve chilled with Doritos.

title: annual blueberry cake
directions: In cake pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch), melt 1 tablespoon butter; sprinkle the brown sugar evenly into pan.
Spoon blueberries over sugar.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream 1/4 cup butter with the granulated sugar; beat in egg with vanilla and lemon rind.
Gently beat in flour mixture, alternately with milk; beat until smooth.
Pour over berries.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center of batter comes out clean.
Cut in squares in pan and serve warm with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: In large saucepan, combine corn syrup and brown sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until well mixed.
Add Rice Krispies until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.
Yields 24 squares.

title: bean dip
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and black olives.
Layer as follows-beans, guacamole, onions.
Tomatoes, peppers, and top with cheese.

title: venison goulash(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute venison, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil until onions are transparent.
Add tomatoes, sauce and seasonings. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add macaroni.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger, then add the five remaining ingredients.
Put in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add warm milk, egg and oil.
Mix in flour, 2 cups at a time.
Knead dough 6 to 8 minutes. Divide dough in 1/2.
Put in greased bowl and let rise for 1 to 2 hours.
Spread in pans and let rise 15 minutes.
Top with favorite topping.

title: mom's chicken continental
directions: Flour chicken and brown.
Remove and drain.
Stir soup, seasonings and water into drippings.
Cook and stir to a boil. Spread rice in 1 1/2-quart size casserole dish. Pour all but 1/2 can of soup mixture over rice and stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and rest of soup mixture.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small cubes.
In large mixing bowl combine all ingredients until thoroughly coated with yogurt.
Use scoop to spoon onto lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with paprika or additional almonds just before serving.
Adjust yogurt accordingly. May need more or less depending on desired consistency.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1 cup pecans. Sprinkle other pecans on wax paper.
Roll cheese into balls. Cover with nuts.
Roll in foil and freeze.
Keep in freezer until 4 hours before serving.

title: cornflake bars
directions: Heat peanut butter and syrup.
Add sugar.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Gradually add cornflakes.
Stir together until well coated.
Butter cake pan lightly.
Press into cake pan. Let cool and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Makes 1 gallon dry mix.
Add to 1 cup hot water to taste.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook onion, garlic and beef until lightly brown.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until thick (approximately 1 hour).
Reserve small amount of sauce.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Arrange layer of noodles on bottom of pan, then spoon sauce on.
Next, Ricotta or cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat, finish with noodle layer.
Spread with reserved sauce and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: brownies
directions: Mix
margarine,
sugar	and
eggs together.
Add flour, cocoa and
salt.	Beat
until fluffy.
Mix in vanilla and nuts with a spoon.
Pour into greased 12-inch Dutch oven.
Bake 50 minutes with 20 coals on top and 6 coals on the bottom.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Pour boiling water on jello.
Then add the oranges, pineapple and orange juice.
Pour into a mold.
Mix the lemon pudding and cold milk.
Add the whipped cream.
Serve over the molded salad.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Frost top or sprinkle with sugar; can leave plain, also, it's your choice!

title: popcorn salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Before serving add 1 cup mayonnaise (thin with milk) and coat well.
Add 8 cups popped popcorn.
Stir well.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and heat to boiling point. Cool by adding cold water.
Blend in egg.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Put in bowl with flour.
Mix with spoon, cover and let rise until double.
Stir down.
Spoon in muffin pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave 8 minutes.
Add oleo and melt in broccoli.
Add onion, cottage cheese and eggs.
Add muffin mix last.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: amish recipe for lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef in garlic and oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt and oregano.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles. Alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella, cheese, cottage cheese, meat mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat, onions, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
In large mixing bowl, place meat mixture and mix well.
Cook manicotti noodles in large pan of boiling water 10 minutes; drain hot water gently.
Add cold water.

title: wassail(old english in the fifth century)
directions: In a large kettle, combine sugar, nutmeg, ginger, cloves, mace, allspice, cinnamon and water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add sherry and simmer over low heat.
Beat egg whites and yolks separately, then add to the sherry mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in brandy.
Remove from heat and serve in mugs.

title: grilled seasoned chicken
directions: Place chicken in a large bowl or container.
Sprinkle all seasonings on chicken.
Turn chicken to make sure it is all covered well, then add honey and lemon juice to chicken.
Again, turn chicken to make sure it is covered well by seasonings, honey and lemon juice.
Let this sit for about 1 hour in refrigerator (longer is okay).
Grill when ready.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a casserole or plastic pan place part of broken lettuce, celery, peas, eggs, Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise in a cup and spread over ingredients.
Repeat layers until filled to top of pan.
Last layer place sliced eggs on top of lettuce plus mayonnaise and refrigerate overnight.
If you like, mix all ingredients together and toss with mayonnaise. Place in casserole and refrigerate overnight.

title: aunt helen pittman's canned green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients (except beans).
Bring to a boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Pour green beans into syrup; bring back to boil. Boil for 10 minutes and put into clean jars.
Seal with sterilized hot lids; seal tight.
When you get ready to use, drain off liquid.
Pour into boiling water and season as you like.
Cook until beans are done.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Use juices and enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat and dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Add lemon juice and cheese.
Stir well, until cheese is dissolved.
Let stand until mixture reaches "wiggly stage" but not set.
Then fold in pineapple, oranges and prepared Dream Whip.
Let stand overnight.

title: creepy witch's fingers
directions: Beat butter, powdered sugar, egg, almond extract, and vanilla until creamy.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Blend to make soft dough.
Roll into fingers (will rise when baked so make smaller than you would like the finished finger to be).
Push almonds down and slightly into top of finger.
Use a knife to create three "wrinkles" in middle of finger for knuckle.
Bake at 325° for 18 - 23 minutes or until very light golden brown.
Remove from oven. Put red gel around "cuticle" and lightly smudge around with tip of tube.
Be careful not to push almond out.

title: nanaimo bars - the great canadian treat
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in microwave or heavy saucepan. Add egg and stir to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Press firmly into an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Stir raspberry Jell-O, boiling water and raspberries until berries are thawed.
Add applesauce.
Chill until ready to serve. This makes one regular jello mold.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken, onion and celery in the shortening.
Add rice, salt, pepper, chicken broth, water and soup.
Mix together.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Put 1 cup sugar in iron skillet.
Put on high heat.
Stir all the time until sugar has melted and burned.
Then add cold water. Cook down to make 1 cup liquid.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Then add burned sugar and mix with rest of the ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in pan with enough water to cover chicken. Add butter and cook until chicken is tender. Cool chicken and take off bone. Place chicken in a baking dish. Next, mix the stuffing mix, cornbread and cream of chicken soup. Add the chicken broth. (Make sure you add enough to make the mixture real moist.) Pour stuffing mixture over chicken. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet sour chicken with rice
directions: In large bowl, combine the bottle of Catalina dressing, honey and pineapple.
Blend together well.
In an 8 x 10-inch or 10 x 10-inch pan, lay chicken flat and pour the mixture onto the chicken.
Set your oven at 375° and bake chicken for 40 to 45 minutes.
Boil water; add rice and cook for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and put in well-greased pan.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half the batter into a greased skillet.
Sprinkle cheese on top of this.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 400° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Place in a greased pan.
Mix soup, broth and peas; pour over chicken.
Make crust.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 300° for about 1 hour until firm. Makes 2 pies.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Bake roast until almost done or boil stew meat until tender. Cut roast into small chunks.
Add all ingredients; put into crock-pot on low 6 hours or on high for 3 hours.
Serve over hogey buns.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and blend entire mixture.
Spread on a thin, greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jezabel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least overnight.
This will keep indefinitely and it makes 1 quart.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice	onions	3/8-inch
thick.
Soak	30
minutes
in buttermilk	(or ice water).
Combine egg, salt, baking powder, water, flour, lemon juice and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Dip onions and fry in 350° oil.
Drain.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar together, adding sugar gradually.

Cream thoroughly to incorporate air. When sugar mixture is light and fluffy, add eggs, one at a time. Alternately add flour and coconut, blending well. Bake in a greased and sugared loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Roll lightly.
Make mixture of cream cheese, Bleu cheese and egg.
Spread cheese mixture evenly on the bread.
Place 1 asparagus spear on each slice. Roll up and dip quickly in melted margarine.
Quick freeze on cookie sheet.
Cut in threes and store in freezer in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, put frozen pieces on cookie sheet and bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes or longer.
Makes 75.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and add pumpkin, eggs, oil, water and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and add nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 well-greased loaf pans (floured) and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots, drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper into rings and mix with carrots in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over carrot mixture; marinate 12 hours or more.
Drain to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Mix onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise together.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese squash
directions: Scrub squash and cut off ends (do not peel).
Slice to make 6 cups.
Cook, covered, in a small pot of boiling water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish, layer the squash, Cheddar cheese, bacon and croutons.
Drizzle with melted butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and croutons are golden brown.

title: non-alcoholic wedding punch
directions: Make a syrup by boiling sugar and 4 cups water for 10 minutes. Add tea and fruit juices.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over block of ice in punch bowl.
Serves 60 to 70.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans; mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: egg rolls
directions: Put diced mushrooms, noodles, celery, bean sprouts, carrots, ground pork, salt and tenderizer in large bowl; mix together.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Wrap mixture in egg roll wraps (use an egg to help seal).
Fry in a lot of grease until golden brown.

title: suzy q
directions: Divide cooled cake into 3 sections. Crumble with hand 1/3 of cake into a trifle dish or other deep glass dish. Heat opened container of frosting for about one minute or until pourable. Pour 1/3 of frosting over cake layer. Spoon 1/3 cool whip over that layer. Layer cake, frosting, and cool whip, ending with cool whip on top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp roll-ups(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread over tortillas. Roll tortillas and chill overnight. Cut into bite-size pieces and serve with picante sauce.

title: pigs-in-a-blanket
directions: Mix raw hamburger, raw sausage, rice, garlic salt and salt together.
Carefully take cabbage leaves off and blanch them in boiling water until pliable.
Shape meat mixture into rolls, about 3 x 1 1/2-inches.
Roll into cabbage leaf and place in a Dutch oven roaster.
Cover with tomato juice and cook over low heat for about 3 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Scald milk and pour over bread crumbs in bowl.
Add onion, pimento and margarine.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni until soft.
Add cheese and salt to milk
mixture.
Add slightly beaten eggs and macaroni.
Fill a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: Blend corn syrup, margarine, peppermint and salt. Add sugar. Mix until smooth.
(Mixture will be very dry at first.)
Divide into thirds (or desired number based on number of colors used). Knead red food coloring into 1/3, green into another 1/3 and leave the last 1/3 white.
Shape into small balls. Flatten with fork on waxed paper lined baking sheets. Let dry.

title: nova scotia lunch
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Chop finely or process pimento and pepper. Drain.
Toss together.
Pour on white sauce mixed with cheese. Cook in double boiler about 30 minutes.
Serve on toast or patty shells.

title: berries and cream
directions: Mix butter, flour and sugar like pie crust.
Spread on cookie sheet (with sides).
Pat down evenly; makes a thin layer.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden.
Set aside to cool.

title: creamy icing
directions: In large bowl mix butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Mix on high until light and fluffy; set aside.
Mix the flour and milk (a little at a time) in small pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Let completely cool.
When cool, add to the sugar mixture and beat on high for 3 to 5 minutes (no longer).

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, cut up squash, cook until tender and drain thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients, saving half of dressing mix for topping.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish, sprinkle remaining dressing mix on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough (this will depend on moisture in potatoes).
Knead lightly.
Roll 3/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with floured 2-inch cutters. Bake in hot oven (400°) on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 15 biscuits.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add 4 cups flour, spices, egg, cream and molasses.
Mix well.
Add more flour as needed.
Roll out on floured board.
Bake at 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lima bean and mushroom salad
directions: Mix together and garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients; add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done (2 loaves).
Batter can also be baked in round cans.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Cut broccoli into small flowers.
Chop some of the stems so salad has some crunch.
Mix with onions and raisins.
At serving time, toss with the following dressing and add bacon.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add butter, meal and flour, then add lemon juice.
Pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate peanut patties
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave for 90 seconds.
Stir until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
When creamy, add nuts and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and cook 15 minutes.
Cook 1 cup rice, 1 teaspoon salt in 2 cups water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix rice and sauce together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.
Top with cheese, if you desire.

title: peanut buster dessert
directions: Crush
cookies
in blender and mix in melted margarine. Pat in the
bottom
of
a
x
13-inch
greased pan.
Put in refrigerator until cold and firm.
Soften ice cream and spread over crust.
Freeze
until firm.
While ice cream is freezing, prepare sauce.
Mix together chips, sugar, margarine and milk. Boil,
stirring
constantly,
for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; cool.
Sprinkle nuts over ice cream and cover with sauce.
Cover and freeze until ready to serve.

title: adolph's cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Blend first 6 ingredients.
Beat on high speed for 7 minutes.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Pour half batter into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half sugar mixture on top of batter.
Pour in rest of batter.
Sprinkle remainder of sugar mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream potatoes
directions: Mix together soup, pepper and paprika.
In a 9 x 9-inch greased pan, line up potatoes.
Cover with cheese, then cover with soup mixture.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes, uncovered, for 10 minutes more in preheated 400° oven.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, Marshmallow Fluff and nuts in large bowl. In large pan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil slowly; boil for 6 minutes.
Be careful not to burn.
Pour hot mixture into the bowl; fold until chocolate and Marshmallow Fluff melt and all is mixed completely and is creamy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into small pieces. Very rich.

title: roast lamb with cherries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Make several small slits over the surface of the lamb and insert garlic quarters.
Blend salt, sugar and black pepper. Rub well into lamb.

title: cheese krispies(appetizers)
directions: Combine cheese and butter in mixing bowl.
Mash together until well combined.
Stir in flour, salt and red pepper.
Add Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly.
Dough may be refrigerated or frozen at this point, if desired*.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (1-inch apart) onto unbuttered cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: spinach soup
directions: Trim and wash the spinach, using several changes of water. Drain.
With the water clinging to the leaves, place the spinach in a large saucepan. Cook, covered, over high heat for 3 to 4 minutes; drain well. Chop spinach fine.
If frozen spinach is used, cook according to package directions and drain well.
Heat the butter in a large saucepan.

Stir in flour and the garlic clove. Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Add spinach and 1 cup of the bouillon. Simmer, covered, over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in remaining bouillon and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Slowly stir in the cornmeal, taking care not to make any lumps. Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 more minutes. Check the seasoning (the bouillon may be salty) and, if necessary, add a little salt and pepper. Serve hot.

title: apple strudel
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add egg.
Peel 10 or 12 apples and arrange slices in buttered 7 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple plumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients (except apples) together.
Heat vegetable oil; stir apples in batter and drop by the tablespoon in the hot oil and fry until done or browned.
Can sprinkle with powdered sugar or make a glaze and pour over.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix sugar, water, cinnamon and whole cloves in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Add instant tea and heat thoroughly.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Strain.
Heat to serve but do not boil.
Serves approximately 8 cups.

title: waddies
directions: Brown meat with seasonings and onion.
Add soup and cheese. Roll out unseparated squares of crescent rolls on a floured surface.
Spoon a large spoonful of meat mixture onto each roll and "wad" it up so that all edges are sealed.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 4 waddies.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Place sugar, cocoa and sweet milk together in a small boiler on low heat to melt.

title: penne pasta with gorgonzola cheese
directions: In skillet, saute onion, garlic, basil and tomatoes in olive oil. Stir cheese into tomato mixture. Pour over cooked, drained pasta.

title: quick turkey crunch
directions: Spread 1/2 can noodles on bottom of an 8-inch square cake dish.
Combine other ingredients and spread over noodles.
Put remainder of noodles over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter snack mix
directions: Combine Shredded Wheat and chow mein noodles.
Set aside.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat sugar with eggs, then flour and baking powder.
Pour milk in slowly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour into dish. Bake 45 to 60 minutes (covered, then remove cover toward end) at 350°.

title: easy manicotti
directions: Heat sauce and water.
Mix together cheeses and spices.
Spoon mixture into uncooked manicotti.
Pour 1 cup sauce into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange filled manicotti in single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: If desired, add thinly sliced potatoes in the beginning.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add egg.
Slot bottom pie shell.
Add rhubarb; pour mixture over rhubarb, covering well. Cover with second shell; slot air holes.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake, cool and crumble cornbread and set aside.
Combine beans and corn.
Combine onion, pepper, and tomato.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and ranch dressing.
Starting with cornbread, layer in a large bowl: cornbread, bean and vegetable mixture, and dressing mixture.
Store in refrigerator.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco; add sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, milk and flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325° and cook 1 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in and dissolve both sugars.
Put flour and egg into bowl.
Mix butter/sugar mixture into flour.
Put into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Wash beets. Cook in boiling water until tender.
Remove skins and cut the beets in thin slices or cubes.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Just as sauce is taken from the stove, add butter.
Pour over beets.
Let them stand on back of stove to absorb the sweet-sour flavor of the sauce.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix pineapple with juice, sugar and sour cream until well blended.
Add instant pudding.
Put mixture into crusts; top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pineapple tidbits and cherries.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: Trim and peel asparagus.
Cut off tips and set aside.
Cut stalks on the diagonal in 1/2-inch slices.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in order given in a large mixing bowl.
Drop from an ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with hand.
Space 6 on each cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes.
Let cool 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: english walnut cheese ball
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Shape into 1 large ball or 2 small sized cheese balls.
Roll in chopped English walnuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit dip lemon cream
directions: Beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice until foamy.
In medium saucepan, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add 1 cup water.
Mix over medium heat.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Gradually beat in egg mixture.
Return to heat.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped cream; chill. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: mushroom squares
directions: Mix together mushrooms, bacon, cheese, parsley, rosemary and mayonnaise.
Heat oven to 400°.
Butter bread lightly.
Then cut each slice into 4 squares.
Place squares buttered side down on a cookie sheet.
Spoon small amount of mushroom mixture onto each square.
Bake 5 minutes and serve hot.
Makes 24 canapes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco mixture. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Unroll dough.
Press onto bottom and sides of 12-inch pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cover crust with meat mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Add peanut butter, baking soda, salt, vanilla, flour and oats.
Mix well. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let melt and then spread.
Mix confectioners sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Drizzle over top. Cut into bars.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 10 inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together except margarine.
Add melted margarine and pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 400° until deep brown, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease an 11 x 7-inch baking pan with butter or vegetable oil.
Melt the butter in the top of a double boiler placed over simmering water.
When the butter has melted, add the chocolate and melt.
Using a mixer on medium-high speed, beat the eggs and salt in a medium-size mixing bowl until frothy, about 30 seconds.
Gradually add the sugar and continue beating until the eggs are thick and pale, about 1 1/2 minutes. Scrape the bowl with a rubber spatula.

title: pork chops country-style
directions: Lightly brown chops in pork fat.
Place browned chops in buttered baking pan or dish.
Add onion, green pepper and celery to drippings in pan.
Stir for a few minutes before adding fresh or canned corn and tomatoes.
Simmer for a few minutes more.
Add seasoning to your taste.
Spread vegetables over the chops.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
At the same time, bake 1 cup of raw rice in 3 cups warm water in a separate, buttered baking dish to serve along with country-style chops.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour in glasses and serve.

title: breakfast chili rellenos
directions: Trim crusts off bread and butter one side.
Place bread, buttered side down, in baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 2 cups shredded sharp cheese, then Jack cheese.
Sprinkle chopped green chilies over cheese.
Beat eggs, add milk, salt, black pepper and dry mustard.
Beat until well blended and pour over bread-cheese.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Refrigerate overnight (this is a must).
Bake uncovered 50 minutes at 325° to 350°. Allow to set 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Mix about 40 to 50 strokes until well blended the flour, salt, baking powder, chili powder, onion, milk, oil and egg.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan (will be like cake batter).

title: yellow squash au gratin
directions: Heat oil in skillet until almost smoking.
Add squash, salt, pepper and thyme.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Add tomato and onion.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Set pan in broiler 6 inches from heat.
Leave broiler door open and broil 5 minutes until brown on top.
Serves 4 or more.

title: chocolate-covered date `acorns'
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast almonds about 10 minutes, let cool. Stuff each date with an almond.
Chop the rest of the almonds and set aside.

Melt semisweet chocolate in microwave until smooth. Dip one end of each date in chocolate, let cool in refrigerator. Melt milk chocolate and dip the other end in the milk chocolate. Then roll that end in the chopped almonds.
Put on wax paper and refrigerate until firm.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Melt one stick of margarine and add onion and celery.
Cook until tender. Add to bread crumbs and seasoning.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add enough broth to make dressing very moist.
Bake at 400° in a well-greased pan.
Right before dressing gets brown, melt stick of margarine and pour over dressing.
Cook until brown.

title: microwave peanut brittle(club member: luke robinson)
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts in 2-quart microwave bowl. Cook on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes, then stir. Cook on High for 13 to 15 minutes or until syrup separates in threads (300° on candy thermometer). Stir in butter, baking soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet; spread. Cool and break into pieces. Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Add flour and spices gradually to sugar mixture.
Stir in water and add raisins and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, vanilla, cake mix, pudding and 7-Up.
Beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Heat cheese in crock-pot and add rest of ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lazy wife pickles
directions: Clean the cucumbers.
May be sliced, if desired.
In a large kettle, add together the sugar, vinegar, salt and water.
Bring to a boil and turn down to simmer.
Place a head of dill in clean, hot canning jars.
Fill jars with cucumbers.
Add a few slices of onion and a few celery sticks to each jar.
Pour hot syrup over jar contents and put on lids and covers.
Put jar into hot water until pickles lose color, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Set on counter.
Cool. Check to make sure jars sealed.
Store in pantry.

title: seidel punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add ginger ale to taste.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Divide batter evenly in muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 12 regular or 24 mini muffins.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel cucumbers if desired and thinly slice.
Combine sour cream and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Stir cucumber into sour cream mixture.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: jello jubilee
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed.
After cake cools, poke holes in it with an ice pick.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour jello over cake.
Refrigerate until jello is partially set.
Mix pudding according to directions and spoon on top of cake.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until all layers are completely set; serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease pan; sprinkle coconut and pecans in pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box; pour over coconut.
Melt butter and combine with cream cheese; add powdered sugar.
It will be thick.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and Dream Whip.
Make layer of crumbs.
Make layer of cream cheese and whip mixture.
Then add layer of cherry pie filling.
Repeat layers until all mixtures are used.
Cover with Dream Whip mixture and serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add bread cubes (I use 4 or 5 slices).
Add eggs, beaten with sugar.
Add pineapple chunks or tidbits (with juice).
Mix all together in 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine bacon, onion and green pepper in 4-cup measure.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring once.
Pour off fat.
Mix in salt, Worcestershire sauce and cream cheese.
Wash and dry mushrooms; remove stems.
Chop stems and add to bacon mixture.
In 2-cup measure, heat bread crumbs and butter on High for 1 minute; stir until well mixed. Press crumbs on top of stuffed mushrooms.
Place half the mushrooms in 6 x 10-inch baking dish, filling side up.
Cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Repeat with remaining mushrooms.

title: california hot chicken salad
directions: Heat chicken and broth in covered pan over low heat.
Remove from heat and add celery, almonds, pimento and mayonnaise (the mayonnaise blended with the lemon and onion juices).
Toss with fork.
Add seasonings and olives and pour into buttered casserole. Mix cheese and chips into mixture, leaving a little of both to sprinkle over top.
Bake in oven at 450° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate frosting 2
directions: Place sugar, milk and margarine in the saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for one additional minute.
Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels.
Place on the cake while hot.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients except baking powder in a bowl.
Start mixer on low speed until all ingredients are well blended. Sprinkle baking powder over batter and mix.
Bake in tube pan, greased. Put cake in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hungarian stew
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, evenly sprinkle stew mix over meat. Pierce with a fork.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add broth, water, onion, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add sour cream.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Butter pan.
Roll out dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Butter top of biscuits.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: shrimp curry casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken stock and cook until thickened and set aside.
In saucepan, saute vegetables in 1/4 cup butter until soft.
Add seasonings (dissolve curry powder in a little water first).

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel, core and slice apples.
In a bowl, mix apples, cranberries, sugars, spices, flour and cornstarch; mix well.
Place apple-cranberry mixture into crusted pie plate.
Cut butter into small slices and place over apple-cranberry mixture. Place second crust over pie; create vents on top crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 70 minutes until juices flow over pie.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Add peanuts. Stir constantly and cook until mixture turns light brown. Remove from heat and add baking soda and salt. Pour onto waxed paper and cool. Break into bite sized pieces.

title: spaghetti au gratin
directions: Cook spaghetti and place in buttered casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and milk.
Stir slowly until it thickens. Add salt and pepper.
Cut cheese into cubes and scatter over spaghetti.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Pour sauce over all. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cherry burst pie
directions: In medium size bowl, combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Mound mixture into pie crust and freeze until firm 2 to 3 hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.

title: favorite hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion until golden in butter or oleo.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Mix in beans and soup or Ragu.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg and seasonings to taste.
Mix well.
Spoon mounds of potatoes on meat mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Instant potatoes may be used.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease platter first.
The size of the platter will depend on how thick or thin you like your brittle.
Mix all ingredients except peanuts and baking soda in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add the peanuts and continue cooking, stirring constantly, until peanuts are light brown.
Remove from heat and stir in the baking soda quickly.
Immediately spread on greased platter.
Cool and break into pieces to serve.

title: watercress and leek soup
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven; add water, leeks and onion.
Cover and cook about 8 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. (Do not brown.)
Set aside 1/4 cup watercress.
Add remaining watercress and remaining ingredients to Dutch oven.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Spoon one-third of soup mixture into container of an electric blender, and puree; continue blending until all mixture is pureed.
Return puree to Dutch oven reserving 1/3 cup in blender.
Add reserved 1/4 cup watercress to blender and puree; set aside.
Simmer pureed soup mixture until thoroughly heated.
Just before serving, stir in the pureed watercress mixture.

title: maja blanca(corn pudding)
directions: Cook, in saucepan, all the ingredients, except cornstarch.
Add cornstarch, melted in 1 cup of water, to thicken mixture.
Pour in a cooking dish or pan and let set to cool.
Sprinkle with roasted coconut and shredded cheese, if desired, when halfway cold.

title: bass dip
directions: Cook bass in boiling water seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic powder for about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool for about an hour.
Add mayonnaise, pickle relish and jalapeno sauce; mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: carolina corn dogs
directions: Dry off hot dogs and put them on a stick.
Combine all ingredients for batter.
Dip hot dogs in batter and fry in hot grease.
Makes 10 cups of batter.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine thoroughly (not Rice Krispies) in a large bowl.
Place in a large, oblong baking dish.
Top with Rice Krispies.
Bake in 375° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix half of crumbs with other ingredients, except cheese and butter, in a casserole dish.
Add cheese and dot of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nine bean soup mix
directions: Combine beans; divide into ten 2 cup packages for giftgiving.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.

title: toffee (no cook candy)
directions: Melt chips for 2 minutes in top of double boiler.
Set aside.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: about 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat and bake for 40 minutes or until brown and fluffy.

title: drop rolls
directions: Mix the Bisquick, milk and cheese together; will be very sticky. Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Melt butter and garlic powder together. When rolls are done, brush on butter mixture.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and fry in one tablespoon cooking oil until brown on both sides.
Makes about 12 (3-inch) patties.

title: hog head cheese
directions: Clean
hog
head.
Be
sure to cut out the complete ear section,
known
as the death bell. This is important that all of the
ear section be removed.
Put hog head in a large pot. Cook until meat is very done, almost in pieces;	then debone. Put the meat in a chopper; chop very fine.	Add all seasonings to
taste. Mix well.
Put in a large glass bowl (Corning Ware is good to use) and press down with some type of heavy weight. We
old
timers always
used the iron to press down, that is, when	we
were not doing all the young-uns clothes.
Press for 24 hours.
Keep cool. Eat now.

title: most excellent yeast biscuits
directions: Milk can
be
warmed in the microwave for 60 seconds on High. Sprinkle
the
yeast
over	the milk; stir occasionally until yeast
is
dissolved.
Put into mixer.
Add the egg; mix on low speed
for 30 seconds.
Add the flour;
mix for about 3 minutes or until smooth.
Set aside;
let rise until double in size.
Roll out
to
3/4-inch
thick.
Cut into 2-inch square biscuits.
Put onto greased pan;
allow to rise for 30 minutes or a little longer.
Bake
for	30 minutes in a 325° oven, or until done.
The biscuit will be a golden brown.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Put persimmons through colander.
Mix in other ingredients and pour in buttered pan; bake 1 hour in moderate oven.
Stir several times while baking.
Serve cold with whipped cream.
Can be canned while hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
The recipe can be halved.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cracker crumbs and margarine.
Mix the cracker crumbs and margarine together.
Put on top.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: date sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread into a well-greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.
Cool completely, then cut into 1 x 4-inch sticks.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Turn into greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bermuda onion bake
directions: Prick holes in onions with fork.
Bake in microwave until tender (10 minutes for 1 onion).
Remove peel from onion.
Add butter.
Serve hot.

title: grape refresher
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Add ice and ginger ale before serving.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: In mixing bowl, put crushed graham crackers, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Melt margarine; pour over cracker mixture. Mix well.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over crust.
Chill; cut into bars.

title: spinach enchiladas
directions: Heat salt in frying pan.
Cook hamburger; discard drippings. Add onion, spinach and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook until spinach is hot through.
Combine soup and sauce in pot; simmer for 10 minutes.
Dip each tortilla in sauce until flexible.
Take 1/2 cup meat and 2 olives and roll in tortilla.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch pan, seam side down.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add Jack cheese.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: bluefish and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In small saucepan, combine oil and margarine; heat until margarine is melted.
Add garlic and saute briefly, just until garlic is lightly browned.
Remove from heat and add parsley and lemon juice; stir to combine.
In medium mixing bowl, combine potatoes, onion, salt and pepper; add half of the oil mixture and toss to coat.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add lemon Jell-O.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Add cream cheese. Stir and set aside to cool.
Combine apple mixture and pineapple mixture.
Pour into a square 9-inch bowl and chill until firm.

title: creole pralines
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir often to keep from scorching.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and pecans.
Beat until almost cold.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Start pouring pralines, while beating, before mixture gets too firm.
I always double this recipe, because they're gone before I finish if I don't!
Double recipe makes 40 pralines.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Place the cereal in a large bowl. Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with wax paper. Melt the butterscotch chips in a double boiler (or 1 small saucepan set into water inside a larger one), stirring constantly until smooth. Then add the peanut butter and mix until smooth. Remove from heat and immediately pour into the cereal. Mix thoroughly. Pour mixture into the pan, spread with spoon or spatula until it is even. Refrigerate. Cut into squares to serve.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix.
In large bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter and one egg.
Mix this until crumbly.
Press into pan with floured fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix reserved cake mix with brown sugar, syrup, vanilla and 3 eggs. Pour over baked crust and sprinkle with pecans.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes more or until filling is set.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Mixture will be hard to mix. Mix until all ingredients are mixed well together.
Pat out in an 8 x 10-inch oblong cake pan.

title: logs
directions: Mix crunchy peanut butter with 1 cup of the powdered sugar. Add
Rice Krispies.
Shape into logs about finger size.
Make a glaze with remaining powdered sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer.
When cooled a little, roll logs in glaze, then in flaked coconut; chill.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: candy
directions: This candy tastes like a Baby Ruth bar.
Combine corn syrup and brown sugar; boil 1 minute.
Turn off heat.
Add chocolate chips; stir.
Add peanut butter; stir.
Add Rice Krispies; stir. Pack into 9 x 13-inch pan, cool and cut into bars.

title: refrigerator white rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of the flour.
Beat well. Beat in yeast mixture and the egg.
Add remaining flour; mix well.
Place in greased bowl, turning dough once.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until needed.
About 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving time, shape dough on well-floured surface. Let rise in warm place until doubled (about 1 1/4 hours).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Measure into bowl the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in thoroughly the shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Stir in milk to make soft, puffy dough.
Round up dough on lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 20 to 25 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown (set timer).
Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a 1 or 1 1/2 qt. loaf dish combine ground beef, milk, soup mixture and salt:
Mix well.
Mixture will be very moist.
Press evenly in pan.
Combine brown sugar, mustard and catsup; spoon over top of meat. Cook in microwave covered with wax paper, seven minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing to serving platter and slicing 3 - 4 servings.

title: lemon jello icebox pie
directions: Mix water, cream cheese, sugar and jello.
Set aside.
Whip cream and mix with jello mixture.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour in an ungreased pie plate (large). Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let set and cool before cutting.

title: harvest bounty casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spread beans and green peppers in dish.
Sprinkle with tomatoes and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over vegetables and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cool fettuccine according to directions, drain.
In a pan, slowly cook 2/3 cup cream and butter until thickened.
Add fettuccine, remaining cream and cheese and pepper to taste.
Stir until fettuccine is coated and sauce is thick.
Serve immediately.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a heavy saucepan. Cook until syrup reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add vanilla and beat until it begins to thicken. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix the oleo, shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Blend red food dye into one part.
Chill both.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon of each color into strips 3-inches long.
Place one red and one white side. Press lightly together and twist like a rope.
Curve top to form handle of cane.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Add carrots and onions. Mash while slowly adding enough milk to make light.
Stir in butter.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with additional butter, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: diet chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in small baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into an ovenproof bowl.
Place bacon slices across top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist. Drop batter by teaspoon into hot 375° fat to deep fry 2 to 3 minutes each side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix to thick batter.
Drop or roll out.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Alternate flour and milk, beating well after each addition, beginning and ending with flour. Add flavorings.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour plus, until done.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Pour all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes. Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Cut the biscuits into fourths with a scissor and shake them in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon. Melt together the margarine, sugars and ice cream. Put coated biscuits into a 9 X 13 pan. Pour the melted mixture over the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Fry ground beef with onion.
Add corn and soups.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Lay potatoes on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with ground beef mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan on very low heat.
Add chocolate; stir until melted off heat.
Add Karo syrup and brown sugar; stir until smooth.
Add eggs; mix until all lumps dissolve. Fill crust or pan with pecans.
Add mixture almost to overflowing.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt the margarine.
Remove and add the next 4 ingredients; mix.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Just spread until smooth and flat.
Melt the chocolate chips, oleo and milk; pour over peanut butter mixture.
To serve, cut into squares.

title: dianne's cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a medium bowl until well blended and smooth.
Roll into meatballs about the size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Spoon mixture over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350° and then place in a crock-pot to keep warm.
Makes about 80 meatballs.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Strawberry pie filling may be substituted for cherry pie filling and you can add 1 cup chopped pecans if you wish.
Chill until slightly thickened. This takes about 1 hour.
Gelatin should be consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Can be frozen.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Saute first four ingredients in hot oil until tender, using a Dutch oven or large pot.
Stir in broth and next six ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces and add to gumbo.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in okra and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.
Other fish may be used.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, shrimp and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook linguine in boiling, salted water, following package directions; drain.
Place linguine in heated serving bowl.
Pour seafood sauce on top.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: white chocolate macadamia cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Recipe may be doubled.
Can also be used with regular chocolate chips and pecans.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Follow the directions and when the pie is done, a crust will be on the bottom, a delicious custard in the middle and toasted coconut will top it.
Put all ingredients into blender, all at one time.
Blend until mixed together.
Pour mixture into 10-inch pie pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Put cut up bread in mixture. Add raisins. When well mixed, put in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. When knife inserted in center comes out clean, it is done.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Whip the Dream Whip and one cup of milk.
Add softened cream cheese and whip some more.
Then all pineapple, fruit cocktail, and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: special garlic bread
directions: Split Italian bread lengthwise.
Mix mayonnaise and onion. Sprinkle in garlic salt to taste.
Pour in lots of Parmesan cheese to make mixture thick.
It takes a lot of cheese.
Butter the bread, then spread on the mixture.
Broil 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Great with any barbecued foods.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all liquid ingredients.
Add all dry ingredients.
Spoon mixture into cupcake papers.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Store in Tupperware.
Yield: about 2 dozen.

title: nutty chocolate
directions: Cook chocolate in double boiler until melted.
Pour in nuts. Stir until mixed well.
Pour on waxed paper.
Smooth out thin. Let cool.
Break in suitable pieces.
It's good.

title: jane's breakfast souffle
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in heavy skillet, drain on paper towels. Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: ponderosa pesto
directions: Blend basil, garlic, salt and nuts on high speed until finely chopped.
Add oil slowly.
Add cheeses and blend until smooth (can be frozen before cheese is added). In heated dish, toss warm pasta with pesto mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and serve immediately.

title: cream of chicken
directions: Combine veggies and just enough water to steam until warm. Drain.
Add chicken and soup.
Heat for about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice, noodles or warm biscuits.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all of the above together and chill.

title: mud pie
directions: Grease round pan or pie plate.
Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt, eggs, flour and cocoa in bowl with spoon.
Stir in nuts. Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Immediately prick holes in pie with toothpick; spread fudge sauce over top.
Cool completely.
Add Cool Whip and serve.
Store in refrigerator. Serves 6 to 8.
Great for kids to make.

title: italian country meat loaf
directions: Put ground beef, sausage, onion and egg in large mixing bowl. Strain tomatoes and squeeze out juice (put juice in separate bowl).
Add crushed tomatoes in with meat.

title: julie's crawfish fettuccine
directions: Melt margarine; add onions and bell peppers.
Cook, covered, until tender for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add flour; cover and cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add parsley and crawfish; cook another 15 minutes.
Add half and half cream, cheese, Cajun spices and garlic.
Cover and cook on low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten egg whites and beat until stiff. Melt butter on jelly roll pan.
Coat nuts with sugar mixture; place on pan, spreading evenly.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Stir with a fork every 10 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces. Yields one pound.

title: garlic okra pickles
directions: Pack whole fresh okra into hot clean pint jars.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boiling.
Slowly pour boiling liquid into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Prepared lids according to manufacturer's directions.
Wipe jar rim.
Adjust lid.
Process jars in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Start timing when water returns to boil.
Makes 4 pints.

title: 4-day fried chicken
directions: Combine eggs, garlic powder, salt, pepper and evaporated milk. Marinate chicken in mixture for 4 days, covered, and refrigerated.
On the fourth day, discard mixture and roll the chicken in bread crumbs.
Deep fry in oil until golden brown. Good hot or cold.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook pasta; drain and set aside. Combine Miracle Whip with wine. Stir in soup. Add the cheese and dillweed. Gently stir in the cooked pasta, add salmon. Pour into a 1 1/2 qt.
casserole. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with french fried onions.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
