title: taffy
directions: Boil sugar and water; then add soda and milk slowly then add butter. Never let stop boiling; add ingredients slowly. Bring to boil to 252°. Pour on metal table or marble slab. Pour vanilla on top. When cool enough, pull until white; then cut in pieces.

title: sour cream kolacky
directions: Blend flour with butter.
Mix together yolks, yeast, salt, sugar and sour cream.
Add to flour mixture and blend lightly. Cover with waxed paper and chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar, vanilla and butter together.
Boil this mixture for 2 minutes.
Turn off heat; add cut up marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add chocolates, one kind at a time.
Stir rapidly until melted.
Add nuts now, if desired.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans or 1 (12 x 16-inch) jelly roll cake pan, greased with butter.
Wait until fudge is set before cutting.

title: butterhorns
directions: Scald milk; add butter, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add yeast and flour; beat well by hand.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and place in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: citrus and spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Prepare ahead so flavors can blend.
There will be more than needed for the salad.
Can be used for other salads.

title: double cheese meat roll
directions: Mix meat, egg, cracker crumbs, onions and seasonings with 1/3 cup of sauce.
Pat on a piece of wax paper into rectangle; sprinkle cheese over.
Roll like a jelly roll and place in bread pan.
Pour remaining sauce over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and white syrup.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and salt.
Mix well and add oatmeal while still warm.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper; let harden.
Yield:
36 cookies.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Mix 1 Cup sugar, the margarine, sour cream, vanilla and egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt.
Drop dough by rounded
into sugar; roll gently until completely coated.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten to about 1/4 inch thickness with bottom of glass.
Bake 7-8 minutes or just until set.
Cool lightly; remove from cookie sheet.

title: brownie chip cookies
directions: Combine brownie mix, eggs and oil.
Beat about 50 strokes with a spoon.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly, about 2 minutes, on the cookie sheet.
Remove to wire racks and let cool completely.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: banana cake(yields 48 portions)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla on medium speed for 10 minutes.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and mix on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Then add bananas and mix for an additional 2 minutes. Combine dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk on low speed, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with cheese. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo; mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat 1 stick oleo, eggs and powdered sugar. Spread over crust.
Top with banana slices, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill well.

title: quesadillas(cheese turnovers)
directions: Spread butter on 1 side of tortillas and place on ungreased baking sheet, buttered side up.
Toast at 400° for 3 minutes or until brown.

title: old fashioned microwave caramels
directions: In a 2-quart microwave pitcher or bowl, combine butter, sugar, syrup, milk and salt. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
After 2 minutes, when butter is melted, stir well. Attach microwave candy thermometer.
Cook 14 minutes on High or 245°, firm.
No stirring needed.
Remove from microwave. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Allow to stand 10 minutes, stirring well several times.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 11 x 7-inch pan for thicker candy. Refrigerate until cool.
Invert pan. Carefully tap out block, cut and wrap in waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: hawaiian french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients; chill.
Shake or beat thoroughly before serving.
This recipe is adapted for use with mixed fruit salads. Makes 7 to 8 cups.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Prepare onion soup mix according to directions.
Add chicken to onion soup. Add apricot preserves. Add salad dressing if desired.
Simmer covered for 1 to 2 hours. Serve over noodles.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix ingredients all together, except potato chips.
Fill baking dish.
Cover with potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: red cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage, cauliflower, bacon and broccoli.
Mix mayo, sugar, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add to cabbage mixture.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Layer broccoli and cooked chicken.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and spread on top of chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and paprika on top and cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine gelatin and water; stir until dissolved.
Add orange sherbet.
Let sherbet dissolve in hot gelatin.
Cool.
Add container of Cool Whip and oranges with juice included.
Pour into mold or bowl and let gel.

title: chocolate cake(wacky cake)
directions: Grease the pan and stir dry ingredients into it.
Pour 1 cup cold water over this and mix well but don't beat it.
Spread over evenly in pan and bake.
This makes a soggy cake, sometimes called "Wacky Cake."
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in 1 stick butter. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, adding butter and sauteed vegetables. Spray a large casserole dish and pour mixture in. (Can crumble Ritz crackers on top.)
Bake for 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: hamburger stew
directions: In large pot, put potatoes, onion, chili powder, salt, garlic powder and black pepper.
Cover with water and cook until potatoes are almost done.
In skillet, brown hamburger.
Add to stew pot and add all other ingredients.
Simmer about 7 minutes until macaroni is done.
Stir every few minutes to keep macaroni from sticking.
More spices may be added or decreased to suit your taste.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Spray with Pam a meat loaf pan large enough to accommodate the mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Cut in slices and serve four with potatoes and vegetable of your choice.

title: garlic butter
directions: Mix well; keep refrigerated.

title: million dollar fudge(microwave)
directions: Put in microwave bowl the sugar, oleo and Pet milk; microwave 5 1/2 minutes.
Stop to stir in 2 minutes, then continue time. Take out and add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and nuts. Stir; if it gets too thick, add a little more Pet milk.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Very good.

title: baked pork chops with cranberry sauce(yields 6 servings)
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in melted shortening.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple; reserve syrup. Combine syrup with cranberry sauce; blend well.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir in brown sugar and vinegar.
Add cranberry mixture and bouillon mixture to pork chops.
Cover; simmer for 50 minutes, or until tender.
Top each chop with a pineapple slice, then a green pepper ring.
Cover; cook an additional 10 minutes.
Carefully remove chops with toppings to serving platter.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Drain excess fat.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Water may be added for preferred thickness.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry nut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, butter flavoring, red food coloring and strawberry flavoring to buttermilk.
Blend well and set aside.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk mixture until color is evenly distributed.
Fold in strawberries and pecans.
Blend well.
Pour in a tube pan (not Bundt pan), greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove cake while hot and brush on glaze.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water; cook for 6 minutes. Remove from heat. Add strawberry Jell-O; add red food coloring for deeper red color. Slice strawberries and put in pie shell. Pour mixture over strawberries.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Mix flour, eggs and sugar together.
Add milk, then rhubarb. Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite size pieces in large bowl.
Sprinkle peas (frozen) over cauliflower.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the peas.
Sprinkle dry dressing mix over the cheese.
Seal entire top with mayonnaise.
Chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks and milk. Add milk and egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Top pie and brown.

title: homemade pizza
directions: After mixing dough, let stand 5 minutes.
Spread dough over pan.
Pour sauce over dough, then place cheese and your choice of toppings.
Bake on bottom rack at 400° until dough is golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: fiesta
directions: You may use 2 cans Ro-Tel instead of tomatoes and chilies.

title: fruited oat scones
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; stir in fruit.
Add combined milk and egg, mixing just until moistened.
Shape dough to form a ball.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead gently 6 times.
On lightly greased cookie sheet, pat out dough to form 8-inch circle.
With sharp knife, score round into 12 wedges; sprinkle with combined sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Break apart; serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chunky, chewy banana cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Puree the bananas.
Beat sugar and oil.
Beat in bananas and vanilla. Combine with dry ingredients and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake until light brown.

title: venison stew
directions: Put meat in heavy pot. Season.
Add vegetables and soups. Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: kristine's quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients all together in a large bowl.
Pour into a pie shell or a large Corning Ware.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, no salt.
Pick meat off of bones and save broth. Melt margarine in casserole dish.
In large separate bowl, mix 2 cans cream of chicken soup with 2 cans broth.
In casserole dish, layer dressing, chicken, soup mixture.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used (usually 2-3 layers).
Top layer needs to be soup mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until bubbly and browned.

title: festive yams
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Combine remaining ingredients. Sprinkle on top of yams.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: the perfect quiche
directions: Combine broth, cottage cheese, egg yolk and egg whites in food processor or blender.
Blend until smooth (will be pale yellow and consistency of half and half).
Add Parmesan, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
In medium bowl, place very dry spinach and onion.
Pour cream mix over and mix.
Spray a 10-inch pie or quiche pan.
Add mixture.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Let set 5 minutes and serve.
Excellent with green salad and French bread.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Put breasts on a cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick spray. Coat breasts well with spicy mustard.
Bake at 350° until no longer pink.

title: raspberry swirl
directions: Combine thoroughly crumbs, melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Lightly press mixture into well-greased 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven about 8 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth and light.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Whip cream until stiff and fold with egg whites into cheese mixture.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Place ground beef in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with lid or waxed paper; microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, or until pink in center.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, soup mix, seasonings and sugar.
Cover; microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes, or until boiling.
Stir halfway through cooking. Microwave on Low for 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: heart healthy chicken breasts
directions: Slit each breast along the bone to form a pocket.
Combine onions, mushrooms and 1/2 cup of the sauce.
Fill breasts and secure with toothpicks.
Place chicken breasts, skin side up, in baking pan.
Pour broth over chicken.
Season.

title: vienna torte(make day before serving.  keep in refrigerator.)
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar and continue beating. Alternate water and flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers in moderate oven 25 minutes at 350°.

title: heath bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a cookie sheet with tin foil and spread 1 layer of crackers on foil.
Boil brown sugar and butter for 2 1/2 minutes; pour over crackers.
Place cookie sheet in oven for 2 minutes.
Remove and place chocolate chips on top.
Return to oven for 3 more minutes.
Spread the chocolate evenly and place in refrigerator to cool and harden.
Break apart and store in refrigerator.

title: onion casserole
directions: Butter a flat 2-quart baking dish.
Boil onions in salted water to cover until just tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Line baking dish with toast.
Cover with a layer of onions and cheese. Repeat layers of toast, onions and cheese.
Beat egg slightly and add milk, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Pour over casserole. (At this point, casserole can be covered with plastic wrap and stored in the refrigerator for the day.)
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: beets
directions: Pour water off beets.
Place in a bowl.
In a saucepan, add sugar, vinegar, water and bay leaves.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Stir and pour over beets.
Can serve hot or cold.

title: broiled flank steak pinwheels
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Lay out meat on cutting board; sprinkle with tenderizer.

Season as desired and beat with tenderizer hammer to a rectangular shape. Spread cooked stuffing on meat about 1/2-inch thick and roll meat like a jelly roll, being sure to roll with grain of meat running lengthwise.
Push toothpicks all the way into roll to hold together.
Space toothpicks 1-inch apart starting at 1/2-inch from one end.
Cool roll in refrigerator 1 hour.
Remove roll from refrigerator and cut into 1-inch thick pinwheel slices.
Baste meat heavily on both sides with A.1. sauce.
Place wheels on cookie sheet and broil or barbecue for 7 minutes per side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in large container.
Fill cup half full of mix and add boiling water.
Stir.
Add marshmallows, if desired. Makes 50 servings.

title: bean and salsa dip
directions: Drain the liquid from beans and discard.
Place the beans in a food processor and process until almost smooth.
Add the hot sauce and lime juice; mix well.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix soups together to blend.
Add rice and drained mushrooms. Dot with margarine through rice.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, powdered and granulated sugars, margarine, oil, vanilla, flour, soda, cream of tartar and baking powder. Drop mixture on baking sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Tea Cakes may be rolled in sifted powdered sugar (1 cup) while still warm.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix
together
and roll into balls.
Roll in 10x sugar. Bake on	greased pan at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan at once.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Tang with pineapple juice and pour over fruit.
Mix and sprinkle instant pudding mix; then mix well.

title: never fail dumplins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead on floured board.
Roll out very thin and let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch strips and drop into boiling liquid of chicken.
Let cook 5 to 6 minutes and dip out.
Repeat until all are cooked.
Serve hot with chicken.

title: fruit basket cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Slice cake in half horizontally.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Spread pudding on cake layer. Add pineapple, then layer of bananas and strawberries.
Put top layer over filling.
Frost the whole cake with Cool Whip and garnish with a few whole strawberries.

title: mexican fiesta biscuit bake
directions: In a 375° oven, melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Tilt to evenly coat dish.
Separate dough into 13 biscuits and cut each one into 8 pieces.
Place biscuit pieces in large bowl and toss with salsa.
Spoon evenly into margarine coated dish.
Sprinkle with pepper, onions and ripe olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.

title: egg casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Line with bread and sprinkle with meat.
Combine milk and eggs and pour over; top with cheese. Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: salsa(fresh chile relish)
directions: Chop the vegetables very fine.
Stir in the seasonings and allow to marinate at least 15 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate rice krispies
directions: On medium heat, melt caramels.
Halfway through, add water and butter.
Stir continuously until the caramels are melted and quickly remove from heat.
Avoid over-cooking.
Mix in the cereal, nuts, and coconut.
Press into a greased pan.
Cut when completely cooled.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost done.
Don't overcook.
Rinse in ice water.
Arrange in layers with peppers and onion.
In saucepan, starting with soup, combine rest of ingredients and bring to boil, stirring until blended.
Pour over vegetables, chill.
Serves 12. Makes a good relish for a buffet.

title: tomato pie
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in pan with salt and pepper.
Mix Bisquick, margarine and water.
Pat into an 8-inch pan.
Peel and slice tomatoes.
Layer tomatoes and onion/pepper mix over crust. Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over top to edges.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Top should be browned and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sylvia's salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple, whole cranberry sauce, lemon juice, celery and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix lime and water (be sure to have the lime dissolved in water) and pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours, then drain and rinse well.
Put fresh water over pickles.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain well.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook and shred potatoes; cool.
Put potatoes, eggs, onions and celery in large bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour over potatoes. Mix well.
Let set overnight.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight chicken wings, soy sauce, honey and garlic powder.
Bake wings 1 hour at 350°, turning once and applying more marinade.

title: texas crude cake(microwave)
directions: Melt
margarine
on High power in a 2-quart batter bowl for
to 2 minutes.
With a wooden spoon, beat in cocoa and sugar,
then
eggs.
Blend	in
baking
powder, salt, and flour. Stir
in
vanilla and pecans.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Rotating dish a quarter, turn every 3 minutes. Microwave on	70%
(Medium
High)
power for 11 to 12 minutes until
done. Distribute	marshmallows evenly over hot cake in pan.
Cover
with plastic
wrap;
let
stand
for
5 minutes. Uncover and spread marshmallows over top.
Cool.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in soup kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.
This soup will be quite thick.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Mix melted butter, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper in a small bowl and place in the freezer until congealed.
Pound out chicken breasts until chicken is flat and thin.
Place mixture inside of chicken and fold chicken until mixture is covered. Place in a pan and cook at 350°.
Total cooking time: 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: hawaiian bars
directions: Bake cake according to directions on the package.
Cream together cream cheese and instant pudding.
Slowly add milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Frost the cooled cake with the mixture.
Top with pineapple and sprinkle with chopped nuts and coconut. Garnish with cherries.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve in hollowed out rye loaf of bread. Tear rye bread and Hawaiian bread into small pieces for dipping.

title: lime chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine lime juice, tequila, olive oil, Triple Sec and garlic.
Add the chicken, turning to coat with marinade.
Cover and let stand at room temperature, turning once or twice more, for two hours.
Position rack in upper third of oven and preheat to 400°.
Remove chicken from marinade and arrange on a jelly roll pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake chicken, basting occasionally with marinade, until done.
Takes approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Cut up bananas and place in pie shell.
Pour milk over bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cream cheese roll
directions: Mix in bowl, flour and salt.
Add butter cut up like pie crust.
Add
baking powder, warm water and egg.
Roll out 1/2 of dough into a rectangle, repeat with other half.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with 2 Chronicles 9:9 spices.
Follow Solomon's prescription for making a good boy.
(Proverbs 23:14). "Thou shalt beat him well with a rod."
You will have a good cake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all the other ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Cook fruit and lemon juice together for 3 minutes.
Then add sugar and cook 7 minutes more.
Take off stove and let stand 24 hours and put into jars.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut eggplant in cubes.
Boil 8 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
As you add the tomatoes and egg, also add the onion, bread crumbs and butter.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and grated cheese.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add salt, vanilla, flour and nuts; mix well.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Save eggs until last and blend slowly into mixture.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in
saucepan
and
saute
green
pepper and onions.
Add the rest
of the ingredients and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Use this to baste ribs or chicken.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Take out the yolk and put in a bowl.
Mash the yolks.
Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and butter.
Fill each egg white with this yolk mixture, heaping it slightly.
Sprinkle each egg with paprika. Arrange eggs on large serving plate.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups of flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat milk to 115 degrees.
Add yeast and dissolve.
Add milk to dry mixture and beat well. Stir in the other 3 cups of flour gradually to make a stiff batter.
This batter is not like kneaded bread, and will be somewhat sticky.
Divide batter between 2 loaf pans that have been greased and coated with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans after 5 minutes and let cool.

title: lemon curd(sissy's sauce for mama's bread pudding)
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and cold water in saucepan.
Stir until all lumps are gone.
Heat.
Simmer until transparent. Remove pan from heat.
Combine 1/3 of mixture with egg yolk. Place back into pan.
Heat 1 to 2 additional minutes.
Do not boil.
Sauce will thicken.
Stir in butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and raisins.
Spoon over hot pudding.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cool, debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Mix together in bowl the sour cream and soups.
Add chicken; mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Crumble crackers on top; drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Blend together the brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and pineapple juice.
Mix the ham, pork, crumbs, eggs, milk and salt together. Place pineapple and cherries in bottom of pan.
Place meat on top of pineapple; shape into ham.
Pour sauce over loaf; bake, covered, for 3/4 hour.
Remove cover and finish baking.
Drain off sauce and invert on platter.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Small oblong roaster works best.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly in pan and sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water on top.
Bake immediately for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Spread cooked spaghetti in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip milk with egg and spread over noodles.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain. Spread over milk.
Spread Prego over hamburger.
Spread Mozzarella cheese over Prego.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: 5 pound fudge
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 5 minutes.
Pour over first 4 ingredients until melted.
Pour into buttered pans.

title: saucy duck recipe
directions: Clean ducks. Put half an onion inside each and salt generously inside and out. Place in large pot to tenderize, using pot half full of water and adding 1/2 cup vinegar.
Add peppercorns, thyme, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaves and boil until ducks are tender, but not falling apart.
Remove ducks from vinegar solution, wash and remove onion.
Arrange, breast side down, in deep roasting pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and put a strip of bacon on each duck.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and blend in orange juice concentrate.
Slowly add 2 cups water and cook over low heat until mixture is hot.
Add chopped olives and pour sauce over ducks.
Bake at 350° in covered roasting pan for about 1 hour, basting often.

title: aunt nettie's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix together and add enough flour to make the consistency of a cake batter.
Bake until done.

title: simmered mushrooms
directions: Melt margarine; add onion, pepper and spices.
Add mushrooms. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add flour or cornstarch to thicken.

title: sugar-free chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour and nuts.
Add melted margarine.
Press in bottom of dessert dish.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
Cool completely. Can be set in freezer.
Cream softened cream cheese and Equal. Mix whipped topping as directed on package.
Blend into cream cheese and Equal.
Spread over cool crust.
Blend pudding and milk until thick.
Spread over cream cheese.
Top with another package of sugar-free whipped topping.

title: crescent dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar well.
Add lukewarm water, scant 1/2 cup sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and flour; mix and knead.
Put in refrigerator at least overnight.
Divide dough in 3 parts.
Roll 1/4-inch thick in circle.
Cut into sections like pie wedges and roll up from large end.
Place on greased cookie sheet and allow to raise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake with vanilla sauce
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg and stir in apples.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into apple mixture along with walnuts. Pour into greased 8-inch square pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with crackers.

title: foo yong fritters
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Blend in flour, baking powder, salt, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce; beat until smooth.
Stir in all the rest.
Drop by teaspoon into 1/2 inch hot oil at 375°.
In skillet, fry 2 or 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper toweling.
Serve hot with soy sauce or dip.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread evenly in a round pizza pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with favorite pizza sauce, toppings and cheese.
Bake at 425°
until golden brown on the edges.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and melt 1 minute in microwave.
Pour over:

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, marshmallows and salt over medium heat, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Take off heat. Stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add vanilla and nuts. Chill; cut into squares.

title: ceviche
directions: Dice fish and cover with lime juice.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours at room temperature in covered container.
Drain fish and rinse lightly with cold water.
Mix remaining ingredients except olive oil and blend with fish.
Place in refrigerator tightly covered. Add olive oil to mixture just before serving.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions; drain well, return to pot and keep warm.
Drain clams, reserving 3/4 cup liquid; set both aside.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into an 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze. Cut into squares to serve.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack into hot, sterilized pint jars.
Place a pod of pepper and a clove of garlic in each jar.
Combine other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal.
Okra pickles should stand two weeks before using.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot; stir well.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (all day).
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased and floured pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook the noodles in salted boiling water until tender.
Add the evaporated milk to soup a little at a time, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add drained noodles and tuna fish.
Mix well.
Place in buttered casserole (2 quart).
Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yum yums
directions: Stiffly beat together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing nuts in small amount of flour.
After mixing together, pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for an hour at 350°.

title: ground beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Cook macaroni in salted water. Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together except the potato chips.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle crushed chips on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place into a greased casserole dish and place a little butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: whole wheat pizza
directions: In 2-quart bowl, combine water, yeast, oil and salt.
Stir. Add flour (whole wheat first), one cup at a time, until it forms a ball that can be kneaded.
Knead for 2 minutes.
Return dough to bowl and coat with small amount of oil.
Cover with cloth and let stand to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (20 to 30 minutes).
Spread into 12 x 18-inch oiled cookie sheet.
Top with tomato sauce and favorite toppings.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook onion and celery in 1 1/2 cups beef broth.
Mix rest of ingredients; add cooked onion and celery.
Pour over the top of the roast.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 2 hours or longer after testing.

title: war cake
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the sugar, water, raisins, lard or shortening, the cinnamon, cloves, allspice, nutmeg, cocoa and salt.
Bring all to a boil, then cool.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a tube pan; set aside.
To the cooled raisin mixture, add baking soda that has been dissolved in a little warm water.
Stir together the flour and baking powder and add to raisin mixture. Beat well by hand and turn batter into the greased tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in margarine.
Cook 2 boxes of broccoli.
Mix together sauteed vegetables, broccoli, rice, jar of Cheez Whiz, cream of mushroom soup and water chestnuts.
Bake in a covered casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa mix drink
directions: Mix together real good all the above ingredients.
Use 1 heaping teaspoonful to 1 cup boiling water.
Serve small white or colored marshmallows on top of each cup (if serving children) or mugs.
Put a small peppermint cane in cup to stir!
(Just for color at Christmastime.)

title: deep south soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.
Add a small amount of extra water, if needed.
Serves 4.

title: parmesan "cheesy" biscuits
directions: Mix margarine and corn oil in one bowl.
Mix Parmesan cheese and parsley in a separate bowl.
Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in margarine mixture until well coated.
Then roll in cheese mixture.
Place close together on cookie sheet or jelly roll pan (the pan should have sides).
Bake until barely done following the can directions.
These can be served from a crock-pot set on "low" for a gathering.

title: leftover turkey crunch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Stir soup into mayonnaise. Toss with turkey mixture. Turn into 2-quart casserole. Top with chow mein noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs and tangy sauce
directions: Soak crumbs in milk.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well. Shape into tiny balls; roll in flour.
Brown in fat in skillet. When done, take up and drain.
Put in sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Bake in loaf or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
For holidays, add 1 cup mixed candied fruit.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: patio chicken
directions: Put rice in pan; arrange chicken over top.
Heat soup, water and onion soup mix to boiling.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green string bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup, milk and dash of black pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Melt and boil sugar and margarine for about 2 minutes.
Lay crackers on foil in long pan.
Pour mixture over crackers and keep it stirred to keep margarine and sugar from separating.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder(serves 4)
directions: In a medium saucepan, brown bacon over medium heat (do not drain drippings). Add potatoes and onions; saute about 7 minutes. Add clam juice and reserve clam liquid. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in cream and clams; bring to a
slow simmer. DO NOT BOIL. Serve with crackers.

title: pork chops in applesauce
directions: Brown pork chops
on
both
sides
and	ends in butter, garlic and
rosemary
(in frying pan).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour
over chops in a covered casserole so that chops are covered by	liquid.
Put
casserole
in 300° oven and cook slowly for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Lower temperature if liquid does more than simmer. Long
slow	cooking
is
required
for this dish.
Serves 4.

title: terri's christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save syrup for bananas.
Slice bananas and put into the pineapple syrup for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add bananas before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add oats; blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: cornbread
directions: *If using self-rising corn meal, omit baking powder, salt and soda.

title: carnation never watery custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt together.
Add Carnation milk and vanilla.
Blend well to mix.
Pour into 8 individual custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in a pan 2 1/2 inches deep. Add hot water to pan until 1 inch deep.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a moderate 350° oven or until a knife comes out clean.
Remove from water.
Cool and serve.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: With meat mallet or dull edge of French knife, pound each chicken breast half to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place bread crumbs in pie plate.
Moisten chicken pieces with water, then dip into bread crumbs to coat evenly.
In a 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, add 3 tablespoons hot oil.
Cook chicken a few pieces at a time until golden brown on both sides, about 2 minutes.
Add more oil if necessary.
Slice Mozzarella cheese lengthwise into 8 slices.
Alternate chicken and cheese, overlapping slightly in baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice and chill. Just before serving, add ginger ale and serve over ice.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pepper corn bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 425° or until brown on top.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and diced onion; cook noodles and heat sauce (remaining ingredients).
Grease pan and layer noodles, hamburger, sauce, etc.
On top of last layer, top with grated Parmesan, sliced Velveeta or grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick rice pilaf
directions: Saute onions in butter just until tender.
Pour chicken broth into a 2-quart pan and add green onions, butter, mushrooms and almonds.
Bring to a boil.
Add instant rice, salt and pepper. Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork and serve.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine well beaten eggs, melted butter, and milk. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
After 30 minutes stir.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Melt the cheese and margarine or butter in a large microwave-safe bowl until mixed. Watch this and stir frequently. Mix in the powdered sugar, cocoa, pecans and vanilla. Mix this well and pour into a 9 x 13 greased and wax papered pan. Chill.

title: chocolate ice cream roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar;
add
vanilla.
Beat
egg
whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1/2
cup
sugar
and
beat
until stiff peaks form.
Fold yolks into whites.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt; fold into
egg
mixture.
Spread
batter evenly in greased and lightly floured 15 1/2
x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake in moderate 375° oven about 10
to
12 minutes or until done.
Immediately loosen sides and turn
out on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together; cool on rack.
Unroll; spread with 1 quart ice cream, softened to spreading consistency.
Frost with chocolate gloss.
Roll and freeze.

title: sausage dish
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.
Beat, then stir in cheese.
Pour into 1-quart souffle dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cheese.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: weight watchers congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add orange drink, pineapple and Equal.
Chill in refrigerator until congealed.
Can also add 1 cup low-fat cottage cheese.

title: crunchy peach pie
directions: Place oven rack in lowest position and preheat oven to 400°. In a large bowl, toss peaches with sugar, tapioca and lemon juice. Let stand for 20 minutes or until sugar is dissolved.

title: mom's hot veggie salad
directions: Slice carrots; cover with water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover with lid.
While carrots cook, string and break green beans.
Add to saucepan.
Break cauliflower (or broccoli) into small pieces and add to saucepan. Cook until tender; drain.
Place in covered dish.
Add butter, crushed garlic and lemon pepper; toss and serve hot.

title: fresh fruit plate
directions: Dip apples and banana in lemon juice mixed in water.
Arrange fruit on 4 dessert plates.
Top with 1/4 cup fruit salad dressing. Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs slightly to combine yolks and whites. Add corn syrup and sugars. Melt butter and add to the eggs and sugar mixture. Stir in vanilla and pecans until well blended. Carefully pour into pie crust being careful not to overfill. Bake for 50 minutes or until set. If the edges of the crust began to brown to early, cover with aluminum foil. Cool before serving.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: In large skillet, add oil.
Cook pork chops until done and nice and brown.
Take out pork chops.
In same skillet, saute onions and mushrooms in pork chop grease.
Cut pork chops up in bite size pieces.
Add to it onions and mushrooms.
Pour can of mushroom soup over pork chop pieces and add 1/2 can of milk. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly except apples and nuts. Then add apples.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham 'n tater casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Arrange potatoes in a layer on bottom and up sides of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: fresh tomato tart
directions: Fit pie crust into a 10-inch tart pan according to package directions. Generously prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Sprinkle cheese evenly into pastry shell and top with 2 tablespoons of the basil. Peel and slice the tomatoes. Arrange tomato slices on top of the basil. Brush with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place tart on baking sheet, then place on lower rack of oven. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining basil. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar in large mixing bowl until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites until they hold a soft peak.
Fold into egg yolk mixture along with grated orange and lemon rind, rum extract and nutmeg.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy chili corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix corn, 3 1/2 cups cheese, milk, 1/2 cup corn chips, peppers and chilies until well blended.
Spoon into greased 12 x 7 1/2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup corn chips.
Bake 50 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Continue baking 5 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.
Cooking Time: 55 minutes.

title: belly busters
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients together.
Warm until cheese bubbles.
Let meat mixture cool.
Put 1 tablespoon in bottom corner of wrapper, fold up, then fold edges into the middle.
Roll over once, then dab with water.
Wet top edge until it sticks.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Eat them until your belly busts.
Reheat leftovers at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Instead of banana you can substitute raisins, dates or pumpkin.

title: cornbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat your eggs, add the oil and sour cream and mix well, add the corn muffin mix and mix until well blended.
Stir in the cans of cream corn.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and orange rind, if desired.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In medium bowl, combine milk, egg and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Spread into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken and cranberry jelly) and tuck into chicken breast under skin.
Brush chicken breasts with cranberry jelly.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: konbu maki
directions: Wash and soak the konbu, kampyo and shiitake.
Reserve the water from the shiitake to dilute the teriyaki sauce.
Cut the konbu into sections.
On each section, lay a strip of pork and a strip of shiitake.
Roll the konbu around the pork and tie with a strip of kampyo.
Place the bundles into a saucepan and add the teriyaki sauce and some water.
Cover and simmer until pork is tender.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onion until tender, but not brown.
Prepare soup with milk according to can directions.
Combine soup, clams, onion, bacon and pepper in saucepan.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: corn bread pudding
directions: Trim crusts from bread before cutting into cubes.
Combine all ingredients; let stand for awhile.
Pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, then stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: amber glow
directions: Place cream cheese on a shallow serving dish.
In a small bowl, mix preserves, dry mustard, horseradish and hot pepper until well blended.
Pour over cheese and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Serve as a spread with crackers.

title: calico vegetable salad
directions: Pour this dressing over all the vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: miss hulling's sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water; rinse and drain.
Brown meat in butter, then add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, chopped onions and noodles.

title: chicken scaloppine with lemon and capers
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness between sheets of wax paper or plastic wrap.
Season with salt and pepper.
In large frying pan, heat butter and olive oil over medium heat.
Cook chicken breasts for 2 minutes or longer on each side until white throughout.
Remove chicken to a platter; keep warm.
Pour wine into pan.
Add chicken broth; boil until reduced by half (about 2 minutes).
Add lemon juice, capers and parsley.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: curried carrot soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine in large skillet.
Stir in sugar and spices.
Add vegetables and stock.
Bring to boil, then simmer 30 minutes until carrots are tender.
Stir in milk and heat through. Garnish with yogurt.

title: home made pasta
directions: Hand Mix!! In a mixing bowl stir together 2 cups of flour and the salt. Make a well in the middle of the flour. In a separate bowl combine the eggs, water and oil and add to the flour. Mix well. Sprinkle the rest of the flour onto the surface to be used for kneading the dough. Knead the dough until it's smooth and elastic, about 8-10 minutes.

Cover and let it rest for 10 minutes. Dough can be refrigerated for 3 days or can be frozen for longer. Divide the dough into thirds and use a rolling pin or pasta machine to roll and cut the dough into desired forms of pasta. Makes 1 lb.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage you can roll in your fingers.
Add vanilla.
Set aside to cool (30 to 40 minutes).
Stir until chocolate begins to cream.
Add peanut butter or nuts (optional).
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: california chicken
directions: Cut off all excess fat from chicken. Peel skin from breasts and thighs.
Rub baking dish with 1 tablespoon oil.
Rub chicken with garlic.
Place skin side down in dish.
sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Combine remaining oil, lemon juice, honey, oregano, thyme and red pepper.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn pieces over and bake another 20 minutes.
(Decrease cooking time by 10 minutes if using breasts only.)
Baste chicken occasionally during last 20 minutes.
Spoon with pan drippings before serving.
Good served with rice or noodles and steamed broccoli.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper, sweet pickles and eggs.
Mix all together with salad dressing to taste.

title: cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Spread over your favorite bread (rye is good).
Cut off crust and cut in squares or triangles. Refrigerate briefly to make cutting easier.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring sugar, water and vinegar to boil.
Process for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift in flour and oats.
Spread
in prepared pan 26 x 18-inches.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Top pie with reserved nuts before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes and toothpick comes out clean.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test cake at about 45 minutes.

title: mapley carrots
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine carrots, water and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook, covered, over medium heat, until tender.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Serve with sauce spooned over.
Makes 2 cups.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in boiler.
Cook until soft boil stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then pour half the mixture over egg whites and beat.
Cook rest of mixture until hard stage, then pour rest over egg white mixture.
Add vanilla and beat until ready to drop by teaspoon on wax paper or greased pan.
Use candy thermometer.

title: cheesy artichoke niblets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon of artichoke marinade.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased 8-inch pan for 30 minutes at 375°.
Cut into small squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Use unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased pan (9 x 13-inches).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown and done.

title: julie's chicken casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam and place chicken at bottom.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle crackers over top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: spaghetti chop
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, onion salt and seasoned salt.
Cook until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water over low flame until water runs out.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla (if you like raisins, add about 1/2 cup here) and cook over low flame until rice is of oatmeal consistency (thick).
Transfer rice into wide pan and cool thoroughly.
When rice is cooled, beat heavy cream (until it peaks and is quite thick) in separate bowl and fold into rice.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and refrigerate.
Serve with Cool Whip on top, sprinkled with cinnamon.

title: homemade potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into pieces about the size of a half-dollar.
Rinse in cold water and put into boiler of water. Add salt to season.
Boil potatoes for about 20 to 30 minutes or until soft.
Boil eggs for 10 to 15 minutes and peel.
Cut up boiled eggs into potatoes after draining water from potatoes.
Add cut-up sweet mixed pickles.
Add margarine and pour small amount of milk in mixture and stir.
You may also add small amount of mayonnaise to mixture and a spoonful of mustard.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: rhonda's candy
directions: Put honey, syrup and sugar in a pan.
Let come to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies or Cocoa Puffs.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Add butter; stir.
Add salt, pepper, cheese, eggs and milk; mix well, then bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, pepper and dry mustard; bring to a boil and cool.

title: zucchini and tomatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut zucchini crosswise in thin slices. Cut tomatoes in bite-size pieces.
Using 1/2 teaspoon oil to prepare casserole, heat remaining oil in a large fry pan.
Add onion rings and cook over medium heat, stirring until limp.
Add zucchini slices, cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, juice from can, tomato juice, salt and pepper; mix carefully.
Turn into a lightly oiled 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes until top is golden brown.
Serves 10.
Contains 58 calories and 3 grams fat. Food Exchange:
1 vegetable exchange per serving plus 1/2 fat exchange.
Good for diabetics.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and add sugar, corn syrup and oats.
Blend well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
If desired, top with chopped pecans.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until set.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to boil in large pot; cook until tender, do not overcook and do not drain.
Simmer next 3 ingredients in separate pot until thick, stirring constantly. Add milk mixture to potato mixture.
Microwave carrots in a little water for 6 minutes to soften.
Add to soup mixture.
Add cheese to soup mixture (more cheese the better).
Be sure to use a large pot; makes a lot.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: First Layer:
Mix together flour, margarine and pecans until crumbling.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes, until lightly golden.
Cool.

title: miniature peanut butter bars
directions: Combine butter, sugars, egg, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
In separate bowl combine flour, baking
soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Cover dough and chill.
When cold enough to handle easily, roll in small (walnut size) balls.
Place each ball in greased miniature muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; gently press one peanut butter cup into each cookie.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Beat with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually add Cool-Whip and powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Put in crust and freeze for 8 hours or overnight.

title: tomato pie
directions: Line baking dish with half of the biscuits; fry onion and pepper in margarine. Layer mixture over biscuits. Add slices of tomatoes. Mix cheese and Miracle Whip; spread on top of tomatoes. Add remainder of biscuits. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: easter bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Heat milk and 2 tablespoons margarine until warm.
Add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: tami's corn casserole
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese, and then mix together with sugar and green chilies. Add corn to mixture and pour into casserole dish.

title: meat loaf italian
directions: Combine beef, egg, oats and onion with 1/3 cup of the tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well and shape into a flat rectangle about 10 x 12-inch on waxed paper.
Sprinkle cheese in center of rectangle.
Roll like a jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Drain off excess fat.
Pour on remaining tomato sauce.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pork chops dijon
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
In a small bowl, combine salad dressing, mustard and pepper.
Brush both sides of chops with mixture.
In a 12-inch skillet, cook chops in vegetable oil, covered, over medium-low heat for 20 minutes.
Turn chops; add sliced onions.
Cook, covered, 5 to 10 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: oven hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add raw carrots and potatoes.
Mix soup and water and pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for two hours at 300°.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients together and make into a ball.
Roll in crushed pecans and chill.
Best when made at least one or more days before serving.
Serve with fancy crackers.

title: chicken livers supreme
directions: Wash and dry chicken livers.
Brown livers in butter in chafing dish or skillet.
Add salt, pepper, parsley, and Vermouth. Simmer 10 minutes.	Serve in chafing dish with toothpicks.	Serves 8-10.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put in bowl the oats, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla.
Put in pan and bring to a boil the sugar, milk and butter.
When this mixture comes to a boil, mix in dry ingredients.
Drop onto foil; let cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Pour in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add B & M baked beans.
Sprinkle in brown sugar.
Add catsup, salt and pepper.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican chili goo(stew)
directions: Saute onion, spices, broth and tomatoes.
Bring to boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans; simmer 30 minutes longer. Meanwhile, saute green peppers.
Add peppers, chicken, chocolate, salt and Tabasco.
Serve in a tortilla lined bowl; top with grated cheese, sour cream and black olives.

title: orange slice candy
directions: Mix together candy (cut in very small pieces), coconut, pecans and milk.
Bake in greased pan at 275° for 30 minutes.
Spoon out into powdered sugar.
Roll in balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into bite-size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: home style onion rings
directions: Take large onion, cut into slices, then separate into individual rings.
Mix 2 cups of milk with 2 whole eggs into medium bowl.
Add a pinch of salt and pepper.
Dip rings into batter and then coat with flour.
Put rings on a flat pan and place in freezer for approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from freezer and place again into egg batter.

title: five pounds creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo or butter in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and boil 8 to 9 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.
In large bowl, combine Marshmallow Creme and chocolate morsels.
Pour boiling sugar mix over them and mix with an electric mixer, starting on low and increasing to medium until it is thoroughly mixed.
Add nuts and blend in.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into pieces.
Stack into container in layers with wax paper.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter. Saute broccoli and onion in the melted butter. Add soup.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Add rice and cheese and mix well.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, melt Nestle bars and butter.
Add condensed milk, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Stir 10 minutes while heating.
Continue cooking 20 minutes, without stirring, then add milk.

title: layered casserole
directions: Put ingredients in casserole dish in order listed.
Put water in to bottom of hamburger.
Top with bacon slices.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered, and then cook 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces. Cook spaghetti. Combine with chicken and remaining ingredients. Transfer to greased pan. Bake at 350 degrees until hot. Add cheese and brown.

title: shipwreck stew(from my mother, fran seaton.)
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Arrange in Dutch oven as follows: meat, beans, vegetables, macaroni and rice.
Repeat, but end with third layer of meat on top, then pour on tomatoes and finally juice until it is almost to the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
If juice begins to bubble over, remove with a spoon so it will not be so tempted.
You may salt each veggie layer if you're not concerned about sodium.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Grease 12 muffin cups; 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Let muffins cool a few minutes.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Roll tops of muffins in melted butter then roll tops in sugar mixture.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place round steak in flour to coat both sides.
Put oil in a skillet and brown steak on both sides.
Add all ingredients to a baking dish and bake for 3 hours in 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off grease.
Put crushed crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan on bottom.
Layer sausage and cheese in pan.
Beat eggs; add milk and mustard to eggs.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white bean & tuna salad
directions: Prepare vinaigrette:
Whisk together garlic, mustard, salt, pepper & vinegar.
Whisking constantly, drizzle in oil and whisk until thick.
Set aside.
Combine beans, onion, olives and parsley.
Add tuna and vinaigrette.

title: corn chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Heat to blend flavors. Garnish with butter, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Add hot water, lemon juice, sugar and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator until thick.
Cut angel food cake into thin slices (or in pieces).
Line round bowl, tube pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with wax paper.

title: buttermilk raisin muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg.
Add buttermilk and shortening.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands.
Spoon quarter-size balls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut crust off bread then cut in rectangular halves.
Spread cream cheese, then roll.
Wrap the roll with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Broil in oven until brown.
Put oven on broil and put pan on second rack.

title: date balls
directions: Over low heat, melt butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add dates; cook and stir 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add rest of ingredients except coconut.
Let cool; roll into balls, then into coconut.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: carrots and cheese dish
directions: Before you bake it, stir 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and you can put toasted almonds on top.
Also heat a can of mushroom soup and serve as a gravy.
You will like it and it's pretty. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can fix day before and refrigerate until ready to bake.

title: italian sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, garlic, sugar, red pepper and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and mushrooms.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over warm rice.

title: spicy zucchini bran muffins
directions: In large bowl stir together bran cereal, zucchini, milk, egg, sugar and oil.
Set aside; let stand until cereal softens in 2 to 4 minutes.
In small bowl mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger; add flour mixture to bran mixture.
Stir just until combined.
Evenly divide batter among 12 greased muffin cups. Bake in 375° oven until brown; about 30 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and molasses until smooth.
Sift together remaining ingredients; add to sugar mixture.

title: cream cheese chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with mallet.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and salt.
Place a block of cream cheese in center of each breast and roll up, using toothpicks to secure.
Wrap a piece of bacon around each breast.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: Place apples in melted butter in skillet.
Add brown sugar and lemon juice.
Cook and stir until apples are coated.
Reduce heat; cover and cook on medium low for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix these ingredients.
Add 4 sliced bananas and 1 (15 ounce) can crushed pineapple.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: skyler's taffy apples
directions: In a heavy pan, combine all but margarine and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until it reaches 230°. Remove from heat for 5 minutes, then stir in margarine and vanilla.
Dip apples to coat well and place on wax paper on buttered surface.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Mix.
Make balls and press down.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg into a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, eggs and orange juice; beat until smooth.
Stir in the orange peel and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: grandpa's mustard sauce
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
(Make a paste of cream, flour and mustard to lessen lumps.)
Cook slowly in double boiler*, stirring until thick, adding vinegar a little at a time.
Great on ham, macaroni and cheese, green beans or even an omelet.

title: fondant for easter eggs
directions: Mix potatoes and butter until smooth.
Let cool.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Shape into balls the size of small eggs.
Chill 1 hour. Dip in chocolate coating.
Keep cold.
You may add cake coloring to fondant.

title: turkey salad burritos
directions: Mix, spread into flour tortillas.
Serve with sauce.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Cream butter and add brown sugar. Add beaten egg yolks.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine oleo and crumbs; pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat eggs for 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, butter and vanilla; beat 5 minutes more.
Spread over crumbs and chill.
Spread pineapple and sliced bananas over other layer.
Add topping, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.

title: greek dressing
directions: Combine lemon, water and dressing; shake.
Add oil, cheese and oregano; mix well.
Makes 1 cup.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer zucchini, onion and tomatoes in a casserole dish.
Add pepper and oil.
Pour tomato soup mixture over top and bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sugar.
Sprinkle sugar over top. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix well and enjoy.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Combine all vegetables and soup; mix well.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Mix all ingredients together in fondue pot; serve with cubes of French bread, if desired.

title: hog's head stew(100 years old)
directions: Cook the meat until it comes easily off the bones.
Cool. Remove the meat and grind it up (or run through a food chopper) together with the other ingredients.

title: cheese balls
directions: Chop mushrooms, beef, olives and onions.
Mix well with cream cheese. Roll into 2 balls.
(If you want to use pecans, chop them and roll cheese balls in them.)
Let cheese balls sit overnight in the refrigerator for ingredients to gel. Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: fluffy frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese on low speed until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk.
Fold in whip topping and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.

title: pepper relish
directions: In food processor, grind peppers and onions.
Scald with boiling water.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and salt.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Pour into scalded jars and seal tight.

title: brownies deluxe
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa, flour, salt and vanilla.
Blend quickly.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crusty crab burgers with red pepper slaw
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the crabmeat, scallions, mustard, mayonnaise, hot pepper sauce, cayenne and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Gently fold in 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs. Form the mixture into 4 patties. Refrigerate for about 10 minutes to set.

title: oconto barbecue beef
directions: Cook ground chuck and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken tinola
directions: Saute garlic, ginger and onion.
Add chicken.
Simmer until chicken is tender; add papaya.
Cook slightly until done but still firm.
Add salt and marungoy leaves prior to removing from fire. Then serve.

title: chicken florentine quiche
directions: Prick pie shell with fork; bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan, stir flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot tap water over batter.
Immediately place in oven and bake 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Place on plate and top with a dip of frozen yogurt. Spoon fudge sauce from bottom of cake pan and pour over top. Makes 16 servings.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Mix well.
Cook in an electric frying pan on low.
Stir constantly until it forms a ball.
Knead until smooth.
Keep in a Ziploc bag or covered container.

title: chocolate pudding frosting
directions: Combine pudding, milk and butter in saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Cool 15 minutes. Add vanilla and blend in confectioners sugar. Add hot water.
Mix well. Frosts top of one 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: pasta salad with ham
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling, salted water until just done, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain; rinse in cold water and drain again.
Transfer to a bowl.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Use 2-quart rectangle Pyrex ovenware.
Cook and drain sausage. Mix eggs, milk, spices, cheese and mustard.
Put into casserole. Add sausage and bread cubes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until firm in center.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 12 deep custard cups or 16 muffin cups.
Measure all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Stir with fork until smooth.
Fill custard cups half full, muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 25 minutes; lower temperature to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until deep golden brown.
Remove from cups immediately (or serve from pan).
Serve hot.
Makes 12 to 16 popovers.
Serves 6 to 8.
Easy and everybody raves about them.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Add water to Jell-O until dissolved, then add frozen raspberries and stir until defrosted.
Add lemon juice and applesauce and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of Jell-O mixture into mold and set until firm.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Put mixture on top of set Jell-O.
Add rest of Jell-O and let set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in bowl.
Mix last three ingredients and pour over salad.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.
In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, heat white chocolate and milk, stirring frequently, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender and serve right away.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Butter baking dish.
Cut green peppers in half lengthwise. Remove the stems, membranes, and seeds.
In a saucepan, boil the peppers in water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in the prepared baking dish.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and butter to pumpkin mix until well blended.
Stir in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf, unless you double the recipe.

title: chicken stock
directions: Clean vegetables and cut larger ones into several pieces. Place all ingredients in a 4-quart slow cooker and cover with water to within 1-inch of the top of crock.
Set the cooker on auto-shift or high for several hours, then change to low.
Cook for 16 to 30 hours.
With large, slotted spoon, strain out and discard all solids.
Ladle stock through fine tea strainer into a large (3-quart) bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours to allow fat to harden.
Remove and discard fat.
Ladle stock into containers and freeze.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 quarts.

title: 30 minute minestrone
directions: Mix bouillon cubes with water.
Combine all ingredients, except pasta; boil gently for 30 minutes.
Add pasta the last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs lightly; mix with corn and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly with corn and eggs.
Pour in greased casserole; set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in a greased 1-quart casserole; set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter; medium heat. Stir in flour until smooth.
Slowly add milk; continue stirring until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add cheese, salt and pepper. Stir until the cheese melts.
Pour over potato mixture and gently mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (bubbly).
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 2 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a square.
Top with cocktail sauce.

title: sausage and lentil soup
directions: Remove skin from sausage and cut into bite sized pieces. Saute in olive oil until lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Add the carrots, celery and onion and saute until lightly browned. Add garlic and cook a few minutes more.
In a large kettle (4 to 6 quarts) combine all ingredients except basil.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer very gently for 1 1/4 to 2 hours.
Stir in fresh basil during last half hour.
If thicker soup is desired, mash with potato masher and stir.

title: grandma's scalloped oysters
directions: Mix together crumbs and butter.
Then mix rest of ingredients. Layer in a casserole dish, starting with the crumbs, then oyster mixture.
Make 2 layers of oysters and top with a 3rd layer of crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into buttered casserole dish; spread bread crumbs on top with a few dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nasi goreng
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef in oil.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato and apple.
Saute until meat is no longer pink, breaking it up with a fork as it cooks.
Veggies should still be identifiable but tender.
Stir in curry paste or powder to taste.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook first five ingredients in small amount of oil for 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth.
Add chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Salt to taste.

title: egg strada
directions: Cut crust off bread and butter all over.
Place one layer of bread in glass dish (butter side down); top bread with slices of cheese.
Cover all the bread.
Sprinkle the chopped ham over the cheese and add your second layer of bread (butter side down).

title: chicken broth
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients.
Cook for 2 hours. Remove chicken and strain broth; chill.
Discard fat from broth. Broth can be frozen.
Use to cook potatoes, vegetables, cornbread dressing, dumplings or gravy.
Refrigerate no more than 2 days. Chicken breasts can be used for salad, dressings, noodles, soup, stir-fry or chicken enchiladas.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 bread pan. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: cheese potato puff
directions: Place the potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water; cover and bring to a boil. Cook until tender, about 15-20 minutes. Drain and mash. Add 1 3/4 cups cheese, milk, butter and salt; cook and stir over low heat until cheese and butter are melted. Fold in eggs. Spread into a greased 13x9 baking dish.
