Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer or until golden brown. Yield: 12-14 servings.

title: pick up breaks
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream butter and peanut butter in bowl.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add corn syrup, orange juice and egg.
Beat well.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients, rolled oats and raisins.
Mix thoroughly. Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: yummy snacks
directions: Bring margarine and cheese to room temperature.
Mix well. Add rest of ingredients and blend.
Shape into 1-inch thick rolls. Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use to marinate beef, pork or lamb. Brush the meat with marinade every 15 to 20 minutes while it is cooking.
If the meat is soaked before cooking, the marinade can then be drained off and used again.

title: microwave tostado casserole
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix ground beef and onion.
Cover bowl with wax paper.
Cook at High power 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Tilt bowl to remove fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder; cover and cook at High power for 4 minutes, or until mixture thickens, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in undrained green chilies and shredded cheese.

title: hungarian hazelnut crescent cookies(kifliks)
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter.
Beat in the sugar; beat the mixture until it is light and fluffy.
Beat in the egg yolk and the hazelnuts.
Add the flour in 3 batches, stirring.
Stir in the vanilla, the almond extract and the salt.
Cover the dough with plastic wrap and chill for 30 minutes, or until it is firm but malleable.
With lightly floured hands, roll about 1 tablespoon of the dough into a 2 1/2-inch rope shape, then curve the rope into a crescent.
Arrange the crescents 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake them in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes, or until they are browned lightly.
Let the cookies cool on the cookie sheet on a rack for 5 minutes, then transfer them gently to the rack and let them cool completely.

title: greek-style bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover.
Rinse well; drain and set aside.

title: maple nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Beat egg, brown sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly over warm crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is firm around edges and slightly soft in center.
Cool; cut.
May be sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and French onion dip.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brown ground beef with taco seasoning.
Drain before adding seasoning.

title: lea's chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: quickie fruit fluff
directions: Fold drained fruit cocktail into Cool Whip.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt, buttermilk, soda, powder and vanilla.
Add flour, a cup at a time.
Chill for better rolling.
Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream egg, sugar and shortening.
Slowly add milk.
Mix well. Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add nuts.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks (2-inch).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper.
Amount depends on number of potatoes and taste.
Mix lightly until coated. Drizzle with olive oil.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven until tender. but not too soft (45 to 60 minutes, depending on the amount of potatoes).
Can add carrots and onions for extra color and flavor. Apples can be added to keep the potatoes moist.

title: herman starter(sourdough base)
directions: In large (1 gallon jar), mix all ingredients.
Stir.
Check once a day to make sure it is bubbly.
Do this five days.
Divide into four splits; one for you, three to give away.
Do not keep airtight.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Heat first two ingredients until it boils, stirring well, let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine cake mix and jello.
Add water and oil, beating well. Add
eggs
one at a time, beating well after each, then vanilla. Cook
in
a
large loaf cake pan 30 minutes at 325°.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish which has been greased lightly and
bake in 300° oven for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan over low heat for 10 minutes. Serve corn chips or tortilla chips. Add lettuce, tomato, onions, grated cheese, sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: janette's summer squash casserole
directions: Put squash, green onions, and water in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Stir eggs into hot mixture.
Stir in 1/4-cup butter (remainder to be used later), milk, 1 cup crackers (remainder to be used later), salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 8x8-inch baking dish.

title: light and fluffy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix
brown
sugar,
soy sauce, garlic powder and orange juice together.
Pour
over
chicken wings and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn chicken wings over after 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate yogurt melts
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Heat meat together with remaining ingredients (except for chips and cheese).
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish as follows:
chips, meat sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese is bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, vanilla and milk in a bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by 2 tablespoon-size onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Makes 2 1/4 dozen.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cut cooked chicken into small pieces.
Spread chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and onion.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese and half of crushed chips.
Mix undiluted soups and Ro-Tel together (mash tomatoes with a fork).
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Add rest of cheese and end with chips.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: wine cooler
directions: Mix and freeze; fill glass 3/4 full.
Add crushed ice and wine cooler; fill with 7-Up.

title: potato boats
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake scrubbed and pricked potatoes for approximately 1 hour or microwave 15 minutes on High.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop centers in bowl with butter.
Save potato shells. Mash potatoes and beat until fluffy.
Add cheese, sour cream, chives and bacon; season to taste.
Fill shells with mixture and bake 20 minutes or microwave 5 minutes on High.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, onions and radishes in a bowl.
Add peas, still frozen.
Toss with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper (while tossing) to taste.
May be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: easy hot rolls(burp bread)
directions: Pour
all flour into Tupperware Fix-N-Mix bowl.
Make a well in the center, take a portion of the scalded milk and all the water
and mix together.
Dissolve yeast in this mixture. Add rest
of the milk.	Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add to yeast mixture.
Pour
into well in flour.
DO NOT STIR.
Seal bowl. When
seal	pops
up,
add	melted	oleo to well.
Stir mixture with
flour.
Re-seal
and	burp bowl.
When top pops again, punch
out	the
dough
on	floured
board; shape into loaves, rolls, etc.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until done. Yields 24 large dinner rolls.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: potato balls
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, bacon, butter, green onion and salt. Chill in refrigerator.
Shape potato mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll in flour, dip in egg and roll in flour again.
Deep fry.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix butter and sour cream until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour; stir until blended.
Spoon batter into ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: easter bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325 ° 25 minutes or until done.

title: fudge sundae sauce
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook 1 hour over boiling water.
Beat in the evaporated milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Keep in refrigerator. Warm over hot water to serve.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Mix cereal and peanut butter.
Press in 9-inch pie pan. Freeze.
Pour mousse into pan.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: condensed milk(sweetened)
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix sugar, butter and water.
Microwave on High 2 minutes until mixture boils, stirring every 30 seconds. Pour over dry milk and beat until the mixture looks like condensed milk.

title: chicken pops
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, cheese, paprika, salt, oregano, garlic salt, mustard and onion.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; dip into flour mixture.
Fry pieces in 1/4-inch of oil at 365° until brown on each side.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve immediately with toothpicks.
Yields 25 to 30 appetizers.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add thawed strawberries, nuts, bananas and pineapple. Pour 1/2 of this mixture into a Pyrex bowl. Chill until set. Leave other half at room temperature. Spoon sour cream over chilled half of mixture. Carefully spoon remaining half over sour cream. Chill until set.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut onions and peppers in rings, add to carrots.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cover and let marinate overnight.
When ready to serve, drain off the sauce.
Refrigerate.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy pan; add the onions and stir until transparent.
Add mushrooms and cook for 4 minutes, stirring. Remove the mixture from the heat and blend in flour.
Add bouillon slowly, stirring constantly.
Add bay leaf and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and stir in light cream; garnish with croutons.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Mix butter, flour, sugar and nuts.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan. (this can be doubled, if you like a thicker crust.)
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Beat 2 minutes and pour over first layer.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with more chopped nuts and cherries.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Bake in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook milk and cornstarch until thick.
Cover and cool.
Combine and cream sugar, oleo, shortening and vanilla.
Add milk mixture; beat until smooth and creamy.
Spread on cake.
Melt in saucepan 1 stick + 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add cocoa, hot water, powdered sugar, egg and vanilla. This must be beaten together very quickly until smooth and glossy, then pour over cake.
This sets up fast and cannot be spread.

title: punch
directions: Mix real well; put in refrigerator.

title: baked wild duck
directions: Clean singed duck thoroughly inside and out.
Sprinkle cavity with pepper, salt and poultry seasoning.
Stuff into cavity 1/4 stick margarine and 4 orange quarters.
Put in roasting pan; sprinkle with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Cut remaining margarine into pats and put on duck, under breast skin if possible. Cover and bake for at least 2 hours at 325°.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in saucepan. Add tomatoes and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in 1 cup of water for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream together shortening and 2 cups of sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and walnuts.
Stir in raisins and water.

title: eggless, milkless and butterless cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan; boil 3 minutes and let cool.
When cold, add 1 teaspoon soda dissolved in a little hot water.
Add flour and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a square pan.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease or line with paper 30 - 36 cupcake (3 pans).
Mix thoroughly shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and the egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 10 -12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Pour into casserole.
Mix together crackers and butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° (30 to 35 minutes).

title: honey lemon yogurt muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a muffin tin.
Melt butter and honey together.
Remove from heat.
Beat together yogurt, egg, lemon juice and rind.
Add butter and honey mixture.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Make a well in the center and add wet ingredients.
Stir just to combine; gently fold in nuts. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 25 minutes or until done.

title: four minute brownie pie
directions: Place eggs, sugar, flour, margarine, cocoa, vanilla and salt in a small mixer bowl. Beat 4 minutes. Stir in nuts and pour into greased 8-inch pie pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done. Pie will settle like a meringue when cool.
Cut in wedges and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add oil, eggs, one at a time, and sugar.
Mix well.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Add apples, vanilla, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Break chicken into large chunks and place over broccoli in a 3-quart baking dish.
Mix undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
(You can also sprinkle the bread crumbs tossed in 1 tablespoon melted butter on top.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or Tetrazzini type noodles. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bake in a 15 x 12 1/2-inch jelly roll pan following directions on box.

title: party hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for about 4 hours.

title: pecan crunch
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk until light in color.
Add cinnamon, salt, vanilla and flour to make a thick dough.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over top; press in slightly.
Put unbeaten egg white on top.
Tilt pan to spread; pour off excess.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Pour over Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: spiced nuts from laura's kitchen
directions: Melt butter in pan. Stir all ingredients together. Put pecans in pan; toss until coated. Spread on baking sheet; bake 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: pork and cabbage in pita bread
directions: In 12-inch skillet, cook sausage until well browned, stirring frequently, and breaking it up.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Set sausage aside and keep warm.

title: grandpa's old-time spice cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with butter flavored cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar substitute, baking soda and apple pie spice. Stir in the raisins. Add the mayonnaise, yogurt, apple juice and vanilla. Mix well to combine. Spread the mixture into the prepared baking dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Place the baking dish on a wire baking rack and allow to cool. Cut into 8 servings. Serve with some low-fat/fat-free whipped topping.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt together and then cool to lukewarm the boiling water, sugar, shortening and salt.
Add to cooled mixture the eggs, yeast and flour.

title: apple mallow yam bake
directions: Toss sliced apples and chopped pecans with combined brown sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of apples and sliced yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over casserole and broil the marshmallows until lightly browned.
Goes great with Thanksgiving dinner.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Crumble beef into crock-pot.
Add seasonings.
Add soup mix. Stir in boiling water, tomato sauce and soy sauce; then add celery and carrots.
Cover; cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn control to high.
Add cooked, drained macaroni and cheese.
Cover.
Cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes.
Delicious with cornbread.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dilute with water as can directs.
Serve as fruit drink or add ginger ale to pour over ice as fruit punch.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well and roll dough thin.
Cut with round cutter. Bake 15 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Chop onion and brown in butter.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: seven-layer casserole
directions: Arrange in pan in the order given, then add the can of tomato sauce on top of hamburger.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: lumpia
directions: *One box of wraps contains 50 (2 packages of 25 per box). Double this recipe if using a box of wraps.

title: spicy beans
directions: Cut up bacon and put in bottom of baking dish.
Drain beans and combine with catsup, nutmeg and Tabasco sauce; put half of them on top of the bacon.
Sprinkle onion, green pepper and chopped tomatoes over the beans.
Pour the rest of the beans on top. Sprinkle with the brown sugar and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Add all ingredients to beans and simmer for 1 hour.

title: dirt
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Crush Oreos and layer in desired dish (can use flower pot and place artificial flowers in pot after Dirt is complete), cookie mixture, then pudding mixture, ending with cookies.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make brownies according to box.
Let cool.
Mix up pudding according to boxes.
Crumble candy bars and cookies in food processor.

title: entomatadas
directions: Grate all cheese, finely chop onion, slice olives and drain all juice out of chilies.
Pour enchilada sauce in a bowl (wide enough to lay a tortilla in).
With your hands in a large bowl, mix chilies, 3/4 cheese, onions and 3/4 olives together until chilies are in very thin strips and everything is mixed well.
Add salt.
Heat oil.
Dip 1 tortilla in hot oil (use tongs) until tortilla is soft, about 2 seconds on each side.
Lay soft tortilla in sauce, then in cake pan.
Fill with 1 tablespoon of chili mixture.
Roll and slice to corner.
Repeat until chili is gone. May layer.
Pour sauce over top, then cheese and olives.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, onion and soup together.
Add mixture to cooked broccoli.
Place in a casserole.
Then cover with grated orange sharp cheese.
Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed, then put on top of broccoli casserole.
Bake until lightly brown.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix biscuits from Bisquick.
Toss lightly on floured board until outside looks smooth.
Roll out into sheet, 8 x 12-inches. Sprinkle with cheese, cayenne and pimento.
Roll up like jelly roll.
With sharp knife, cut in 8 slices.
Flatten slightly and lay on top of creamed mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 450° about 30 minutes or until browned.

title: bonnie's hormeli dip
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a pie plate.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yummy!!

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and cream cheese.
Mix well until blended.
Serve with fruit.

title: shrimp dip
directions: After soaking shrimp for 15 minutes in cold water, drain and mix well with other ingredients.
Serve with crackers or cocktail bread.

title: five cup salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours.

title: stuffed strawberries
directions: Remove stems from strawberries. Place point side up on cutting board. Cut a deep X in the top of each berry. Carefully spread each berry apart. In a bowl, beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Spoon filling into each berry. Refrigerate until serving. Makes 24 strawberries. Each strawberry is 17 calories.

title: cheesy chicken and broccoli macaroni
directions: Cook chicken in water with onion salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil; add macaroni.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese and broccoli; stir until Velveeta melts. Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add soda, cream of tartar, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add milk and flour.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: meringue shells
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Add vanilla, cream of tartar and a dash of salt.
Beat to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating until very stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved. Meringue will be glossy.
Cover baking sheet with plain paper. Draw 8 circles 3 1/2 inches in diameter.
Spread each with 1/3 cup of meringue.
Using back of spoon, shape into shells.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
For crisper meringues, turn off heat; let dry in oven with door closed for about 1 hour.
Serve with vanilla ice cream and strawberries.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms thoroughly and slice thin.
Melt margarine and add onion and mushrooms.
(Use a large skillet.) Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and continue to simmer for another 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, butter, milk and cheese together until blended on stove top.
Add onion, rice and broccoli until well blended.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cover baking dish while baking. Two-quart long, flat baking dish is preferred.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Add first 6 ingredients and mix very gently.
Pour into a buttered casserole, top with mixed oleo and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: With hand held mixer, beat cream cheese and margarine until light and fluffy (about 2 minutes).
Add sugar, pecans and vanilla.
Continue beating on low speed until combined.
If too soft, chill about 10 minutes prior to spreading.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade and Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Chill. Garnish with Reddi-Wip and lemon slices, if desired.

title: sausage oven pancakes
directions: Brown sausage.
In mixing bowl, combine pancake mix, spices, milk and eggs.
Mix until batter is smooth; add apple.
Pour into well-greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange sausage on top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.
Makes 5 servings.

title: hot owasso
directions: Pour all ingredients into a large pot.
Simmer.
Serve hot.

title: burgundy beef stew
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients; blend in flour, 1 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and basil.
Add meat and vegetables; stir to distribute through gravy.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours and stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: sauteed squash
directions: Cut onion and squash into chunks.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until onion begins to get tender.
Add squash and saute, stirring occasionally, until all vegetables are tender.
Season with salt or dill.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2.

title: oreo fluff
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix Cool Whips together.
Fold in cookies. Serve chilled.

title: old fashion corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add corn, cracker crumbs, milk and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix in a bowl the sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add fruit cocktail (include juice), eggs and vanilla.
Mix at low speed. Pour into three greased, paper lined and floured cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice with filling.

title: bacon cheese meat loaf
directions: Moisten dry bread with a small amount of milk.
Break bread apart.
Add ground meat, onion and celery; mix well.
Add eggs and tomato sauce to mixture.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Add dash of Worcestershire sauce.

title: barbecue boston butt
directions: Salt and pepper Boston Butt to taste.
Place in slow cooker. Cover with water and cook on high until meat is done and falling apart or cook on low all night.
When meat is done, preheat oven to 500°.
Remove meat from slow cooker and place in baking pan or glass baking dish.
Place meat in oven and cook until meat drips out a little bit.
Cover meat with barbecue sauce and put back in oven for about 15 or 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve. Delicious!

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, vanilla wafers, milk, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan (sprayed) for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: chicken essex casserole
directions: Boil chicken until real done.
Season with 1/2 cup diced celery and 1/2 cup diced onion.
Cool and take meat from bones. Mix all together. Put into 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish. Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Delicious.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Add other ingredients to sifted flour.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Bake on ungreased sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa with boiling water.
Set aside and cool.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add cooled cocoa mix.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and flour.
Then milk and nuts, if desired.
Pour in 11 x 17-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots and add pepper and onion.
Heat a little, but do not boil.
Mix other ingredients in and pour over carrots, onions and pepper.
Let stand 2 or 3 days to marinate.

title: turkey-rice soup
directions: Simmer turkey bones about 45 minutes.
Remove, chop and set aside any meat.
Add celery, onion, parsley, curry powder and cayenne pepper to the stock and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Add instant or cooked rice.
Taste for seasoning.
Thicken with cornstarch, mixed with a little cold water, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix strawberry juice with water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Blend all ingredients together with a mixer, adding berries last.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
DO NOT OVER BEAT.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes, till a toothpick near the center comes out clean and cake pulls away from the side.
Cool in pan 10-15 minutes before turning out. Ice with frosting of your choice.
Makes 12-15 servings or 20-24 if cut smaller.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and dressing
directions: Slice zucchini or summer squash in half lengthwise; scoop out insides, leaving 1/4-inch rim so canoe stays intact.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Cook pork over high heat for about 6 minutes with bay leaves. Add chicken gizzards. Stir in seasoning mix, then add onions, celery, bell peppers and garlic. Add margarine. Reduce heat to medium and cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly, scraping bottom of pan. (It will stick a lot.) Add 1 cup chicken broth. Stir until any mixture comes loose from bottom of pan. Cook about 8 minutes over medium heat. Add meat. Cook about 2 to 3 minutes. Add rice and mix thoroughly. Cover and steam about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and mix uncooked green onions into mixture. Remove bay leaves and serve. Cook rice with chicken broth.

title: squash patties
directions: Let squash cool.
Mix all other ingredients, then squash.
Put in refrigerator for a few minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot skillet.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Add onion. In casserole dish, put hamburger. In pot, mix cream of chicken soup and 1 can water. Cook until mixed well. Pour over hamburger. Add cheese laying it to cover. Lay Tater Tots on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until Tater Tots are done and brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line pie plate with crust.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour in crust.
Top with other crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Cook 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Any salad dressing can be used as preferred.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Chop up liver sausage.
Blend in cream cheese.
Chop up eggs, very fine.
Blend eggs in with salad dressing.
When thoroughly mixed, add onions.
Chill; serve with party rye bread or Triscuits.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute garlic in oil until soft.
Add flour and chili powder. Cook and stir to make a roux.
Add water, cocoa, bouillon cube and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until bouillon cube is dissolved.
Mix together Monterey Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese and onion.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Quickly dip each tortilla in hot oil to soften.
Place 1 tablespoon cheese mixture in center of tortilla and roll.
Place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Spoon sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle with onions and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields: 12.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and add hot water. Bring to a boil, stirring until it thickens.
Add jello and stir until it dissolves.
Wash and stem strawberries and place in pie shell.
If berries are large, they can be cut in half.
Cool sauce in pan in cold water.
When cool, pour over berries and spread with knife to be sure all the berries are covered.
Cool pie and serve with Cool Whip.

title: thin crust homemade pizza
directions: Stir yeast and sugar into 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Set in a warm place until yeast bubbles and doubles in volume, about 10 minutes.
Stir together flour and salt in a large mixing bowl. Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in yeast mixture, 1 cup lukewarm water and 1/4 cup of the olive oil.
Mix until a rough ball forms.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead for about 10 minutes or until dough is elastic and shiny. Grease the inside of a ceramic bowl with the remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Place dough in bowl, turning once to oil all sides. Cover with a cloth and let rise in a warm place for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until dough has doubled in bulk.

title: "no! they're all mine chocolate brownies"
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients together and put into greased jelly roll pan and bake for 25 minutes.

title: sausage and peppers italiano
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook sausage in water 5 minutes or until sausage is brown on both sides.
Add peppers, onion and garlic to sausage and cook until peppers are tender-crisp, stirring often.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and vinegar. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Cook rice. Serve sausage and peppers over hot rice.

title: boiled lobster
directions: Cut celery and carrots into 2 inch long strips. In a large skillet, cook vegetables in butter until crisp-tender. Season with salt and pepper.

title: carrot coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs for 2 minutes.
Add flour mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, carrots and coconut.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dipped candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add coconut, nuts and cherries. Mix well and refrigerate until chilled.
Roll into balls (about the size of a ping pong ball).
Insert a toothpick in each one. Place on wax paper, on a cookie sheet and freeze.
Dip in chocolate or butterscotch.
Place chocolate or butterscotch, paraffin and butter in top of double boiler (don't allow water to boil).

title: nut caramel triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.

title: molletes
directions: Split bread in half lengthwise (use both halves).
Spread with a thin layer of margarine.
Spread with a layer of refried beans. If desired, place thin slices of ham or spread the Mexican sausage over the beans.
Top with grated cheese.
Broil or bake on high heat until cheese is melted.
Cut into individual pieces and serve with salsa (hot sauce).

title: spicy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and green pepper in olive oil in a large skillet, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for at least 4 hours, adding water as needed and stirring occasionally. Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; marinate overnight with salad dressing, Salad Supreme|, onions, peppers and mushrooms. Add avocados, tomatoes and olives just before serving.

title: crab spread
directions: Cream soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Slowly add onion, celery and crab meat.
Heat water and gelatine until thick, then blend all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: fudge
directions: Grease plate or pan.
Mix in a heavy 2 quart saucepan the following:
sugar, oleo, can milk, and marshmallows.
Bring to a bubbling boil quickly, stirring constantly.
Whe bubbles appear all over the top, reduce to medium heat and add semi-sweet chips. Stir until chips are completely melted and blended into mixture. Add pecans and mix well.
Pour onto greased pan.
Cool thoroughly. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: six layer dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise in another bowl.
To assemble, spread bean dip in oblong dish.
Top with avocado mixture; layer with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives; cover with cheese.
Top with picante sauce.
Serve with chips.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Melt the almond bark and peanut butter in a double boiler. Put the marshmallows, peanuts and Rice Krispies in a large container and pour the first ingredients over; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Stir margarine and peanut butter until melted. Add sugar. The mixture will be real stiff. Pat into a greased pan. Let sit for 2 hours. Cut into squares.

title: caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In small pan, melt margarine. Use 2 to 3 tablespoons to coat Bundt pan. Sprinkle 4 tablespoons nuts in pan. Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Cut each biscuit in half and roll into a ball. Shake in a Baggie filled with sugar and cinnamon. Put half of balls in pan and drizzle with half syrup. Repeat layer. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown. Invert immediately onto plate and serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs (add one at a time), flour, sugar, vanilla, apples, nuts and cinnamon, then bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on crackers (your choice) with slice of stuffed or ripe olive for garnish, or pecans.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Put egg in bowl; add all other ingredients except oil and water.
Mix with electric mixer on medium.
Turn mixer to high; slowly add oil a little at a time until mixture begins to thicken. Remaining oil can then be added faster.
When all oil has been added, add boiling water and mix thoroughly.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with cake mix using a wooden spoon. Put in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for at least 60 minutes.
Turn upside-down to cool.

title: "tipsy" sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; drain, peel and mash.
Chop walnuts.
Mix in milk, sugar, butter, walnuts, salt and bourbon.
Place in baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Very rich!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place drained pineapple in a greased casserole dish.
Combine flour and sugar; spread over pineapple.
Spread cheese on top. Crush crackers and spread over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 - 30 minutes, until bubbly and crackers are brown.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1 large box of strawberries until well done.
Drain well. Cook strawberries, berry juice, sugar and cornstarch until thick. Let cool.
Add 1 quart of small berries.
Fold in gently, not to mash.

title: randolph county persimmon pudding
directions: In very large mixing
bowl, blend all ingredients well, adding persimmons and sweet potato last to insure smooth consistency. Place in baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 1/2 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold with sweetened whipped cream.
Cut in squares.

title: tasty beer dip
directions: Soften cheese, add onion, vinegar, garlic powder and red pepper.
Add enough flat beer to make a soft dip.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes a small amount, double if desired.
Be sure beer is flat.

title: coconut cream pudding dessert
directions: Crust:
Crumble crackers and melted butter; mix together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Combine all canned ingredients in a pot on medium heat. Season and brown ground beef.
Drain oil.
Pour beef into vegetables.
Let boil on medium/high for 40 minutes, stirring often.
Allow 5 to 10 minutes to cool.
Serve warm.

title: eric's chicken
directions: Wrap chicken in bacon and one slice of beef and lay in casserole dish.
Combine soup, sour cream and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°.
If it browns too much, cover with foil last 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken breast with artichoke hearts
directions: Rinse artichoke hearts and drain well.
Mushrooms may be added.
Place in buttered 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Add soup and wine. Season with salt and pepper.
Push chicken breasts partially into mixture.
Cover with stuffing and dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and continue baking until brown, approximately 30 minutes.
This may be left in warm oven until serving time.
Serves 8 generously.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop stems.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cook stems in butter until tender; stir in flour, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in crab, egg yolks, parsley and lemon juice.
Preheat oven to 425°.
In large skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Cook mushroom caps 5 minutes.
Fill with crab mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan or use batter for about 20 cupcakes.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
The batter will be thin.
Bake the cake for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cupcakes will take about 15 to 20 minutes. This batter is too rich to bake as a layer cake.

title: four bean chili
directions: Cook bacon in a Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium-high heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon drippings until onion is tender-crisp.
Reduce heat to medium; stir in bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated and flavors are blended.
To serve, top with shredded cheese.

title: three-hour potato rolls
directions: Peel
and cook potatoes in water to cover until tender. Mash them (should be 1 cupful).	Dissolve the yeast in the 1/2 cup warm
water.
Add
the
scalded
milk and the lard.
Beat until melted.
Add the potatoes.	Stir in 1 cup of the flour, 2 eggs, sugar and salt.
Let rise in a warm place for 2 hours. Sift remaining
flour
before
measuring
and stir in 4 cups. Cover bowl with a cloth and
let	rise
in
a warm place for 1 hour.

title: banana bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Before you begin, start your oven at 350° and thoroughly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
You can use a wooden spoon and mixing bowl instead of an electric mixer, but either way, scrape the sides of the bowl frequently with a spatula.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.
